title: hawaiian delight salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and add dry jello.
Add marshmallows to 2 cups hot water, then add jello mixture.
Add pineapple and nuts. Chill until thickened.
Stir in Cool Whip and chill.
(Use as dessert or salad on lettuce.)

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice and drain tomatoes on paper towel. Combine all ingredients except milk. Coat tomatoes with flour. Lay aside and mix the remaining flour with milk. Mix until smooth. Then dip slices into milk mixture and fry in hot skillet until golden brown on each side.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and oleo and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Blend cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and spread over pretzels and refrigerate.
Take juice from frozen strawberries and pineapple.
Add water to make 2 cups.
Boil jello with juices.
Cool and let thicken a little before adding strawberries and pineapple.
Add fruit and pour over cream mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp and bacon brochettes
directions: Cover 12 large shrimp with partially cooked bacon slices. Thread on skewers.
Brush with mixture of oil, lemon juice and salt to spice and rosemary leaves.
Broil, turning frequently.

title: macaroon brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9 pan. Prepare brownies according to package for cake-like brownies. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Put egg whites in medium bowl. Beat at high speed until foamy. Beat in sugar gradually until meringue forms firm peaks. Add almond extract. Fold in almonds and coconut. Spread over warm brownies. Bake 12 to 14 minutes, until meringue is set and lightly browned. Cool completely. Cut into bars.

title: our favorite salad
directions: Wash all produce and drain well. A salad spinner works excellent. Rip both lettuce varieties into bite size pieces. Add onion and toss. Combine walnuts, banana chops, ruby raisins, and sunflower seeds.

title: little pizzas
directions: Brown the sausage first.
Add beef; drain off fat.
Add cheese (no heat).
Stir until blended.
Add spices.
Spread onto rye. Place on trays.
Freeze, uncovered, for about 20 minutes, then bag for future use.
Do not defrost.
Or use now.

title: hopple popple brunch
directions: Mix all together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Can be made the night before.
Layer Swiss cheese on top.
Serves 12.

title: hershey ice cream
directions: Heat Eagle Brand milk just warm enough to melt Hershey bar. Add evaporated milk and vanilla.
Beat eggs and sugar until smooth.
Mix all together and pour into 1 gallon freezer.
Finish filling with milk and freeze.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, salt, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl. Mix with a hand mixer.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add condensed milk and stir well.
Churn in freezer as per instructions.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: hot cheese squares
directions: In 8 x 8 inch or 9 x 9 inch buttered pan, layer cheese and chillies (Monterey, Cheddar and chillies) alternately; then beat together and pour following mixture on top of cheese. 2 eggs, 1/2 tsp. flour and 2 Tbsp. light cream.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes, then let cool 10 minutes and cut in squares.
Serve on Waverly crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Rinse cream of chicken soup can with 1/2 cup water.
Mix ingredients and put in greased baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: matrimony cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; press half of mixture into a greased 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Add filling and spread over previous layer. Top with remaining crumb mixture.

title: round steak
directions: Sprinkle steak with soup mix and wrap tightly in aluminum foil.
On cookie sheet bake 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover last 1/2 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour. Mix with cocoa.
Pour into greased pans until 1/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: island shrimp and noodles
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Line a casserole with noodles and form into a nest.
In a large skillet, saute shrimp in clarified butter until pink, about 5 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover noodles with shrimp.
Combine soup, sour cream, mayonnaise and mustard; add chives and sherry.
Pour sauce over shrimp and top with shredded cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until cheese is bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: bacon cheese appetizers
directions: Slice bacon in half.
Cut Cheddar cheese in small even cubes. Sprinkle cheese cubes with cayenne pepper.
Wrap bacon slices around each cheese cube.
Fasten with wooden picks.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Mixture should be chilled.
Next day, prepare cake according to package directions for 2 (8-inch) layers.
Cut each 8-inch layer in two, making 4 (8-inch) layers.
Turn cut side up; slice off brown layer, leaving cake open so topping can sink in. Spread coconut between layers.
Let stand 3 days in refrigerator. Coconut mixture may need to be spooned on periodically while cake is chilling.
Super moist.
Super good.

title: disaster cake
directions: Bake cake as per box directions.
When cake is cool, crumble up in a shallow dish.
Cover with pudding.
Top with whip cream.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle reserved marshmallows over top and broil until lightly browned.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oil until clear in medium size skillet.
Add tomatoes and 2 cups water, rice and chili powder. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer until rice is done, about 20 minutes.
Serve with pork or beef.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; chill, then roll in pecans.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook your chicken breasts.
Cut your chicken up into pieces (small).
Mix all ingredients together.
Mix in pecans.

title: crusty beef, cheese and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Heat oil and saute onion until golden brown.
Add meat and brown slightly.
Add sauce and heat. In a casserole, layer 1/2 of the noodles, 1/2 of the sauce and 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate rum moon bars
directions: Melt chips and butter with water in saucepan.
In large mixing bowl,
combine
sugar
and eggs.
Add flour and vanilla and continue mixing.
Add cooled chocolate mixture.
Pour onto greased and floured cookie sheet (jelly roll style pan).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Remove from oven and ice.
(Mix last 3 ingredients together.)

title: salmon bisque(super, super dish!)
directions: Place contents of can of pink salmon (oil included) in saucepan.
Add canned tomatoes, chopped onion, parsley and water. Simmer these ingredients for 20 minutes.

title: garlic cheese grits casserole
directions: Add garlic salt and butter to water as it comes to a boil. Slowly add grits, chopped cheese rolls, eggs and paprika.
Stir slowly until ready.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach leaves into bite size pieces and place in a salad bowl.
Add the onion rings and orange segments.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Cook on full power for 2 minutes (should be boiling).
Add salt (should foam).
Pour mixture over 3 to 4 quarts popped corn in a brown bag.
Shake hard.
Place in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes (still in paper bag).
Shake hard.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake hard.
Microwave on High for 40 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes.

title: pink applesauce
directions: Wash and core apples.
Cut apples into large chunks.
Mix apples and water and put in glass dish.
Cook in microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Push apples through strainer.
Add sugar if wanted.

title: ann hendrick's chocolate sauce supreme
directions: Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler over simmering water. Remove top from water and stir in butter until melted.
Blend in powdered sugar, salt, corn syrup, hot water and creme de cocoa. Add vanilla when mixture has cooled slightly.

title: gourmet peach shortcake
directions: Beat together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flavoring. Stir in dry ingredients alternating with cream.	Spoon onto a coated 9-inch round pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a rack.
Prepare Peach Nectar and White Chocolate Mousse and assemble as follows.
Slice cake into 8 wedges and then slice the wedges horizontally.
Spoon nectar onto plate; place bottom half of cake wedge on nectar, and then layer with more nectar, mousse and sliced peaches.
Top with other half of wedge and dollop of White Chocolate Mousse and garnish with mint leaves or raspberries.
Serves 8.

title: hungarian beef roll
directions: Brown steak on both sides; salt and pepper lightly.
Mix hamburger, 1/2 package mushroom soup and 1/2 package onion soup with bread crumbs.
Spread on steak.
Roll up and tie both ends and middle with string.
Mix remaining soups and buttermilk; baste steak while baking.
Bake for 1 hour or until steak is tender at 375°.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour together; set aside to cool.
In another bowl, cream together the powdered sugar, shortening and butter with beater.
Add the thickened mixture.
Add vanilla and pinch of salt.

title: caraway puffs
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add caraway seed.
Heat cheese just until lukewarm.
Mix cheese, sugar, salt, soda and eggs into yeast mixture.
Slowly add flour, mixing until dough cleans bowl. Let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
Stir down dough.
Divide among 24 well-greased medium muffin cups.
Cover and let rise again until double, about 45 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°. Bake about 25 minutes.
Remove from cups; brush with butter.
Makes 2 dozen puffs.

title: pie meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until soft peaks form when beaters are raised.
Gradually beat in sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
Continue to beat until stiff peaks form when beaters are raised.
Spread over warm filling.
Bake 2 to 10 minutes or until golden.

title: best ever lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and lemon juice in heavy saucepan.
(Can use double boiler.)
Add egg yolks, water, vinegar, butter and salt.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Pour into a baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: apple salad (1)
directions: Beat pudding and milk according to directions.	Add whipped topping.
Cut up Snickers bars and chop apples with skins on.
Mix all together.

title: spicy turkey rice soup
directions: Combine turkey, egg white, 1/4 cup of the salsa, bread crumbs and salt; mix well.
Shape into meatballs about 3/4 inch in diameter and set aside.
Combine broth, water, remaining salsa and contents of rice and seasoning packets in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add meatballs.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 8 minutes.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Sprinkle with cilantro.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, onion, eggs, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top with bacon and olives. Bake at 350° for 30-60 minutes. Less cheese can be used, and this recipe can be stored for several days in the refrigerator. It is also good warmed over.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour this batter over butter.
Pour peaches and peach juice over batter (do not stir) and bake for 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Blend in shortening with pastry blender or fork.
Add milk and mix well.
Dip teaspoon into cold water, then into dough and spoon dough onto chicken mixture. Cover and cook quickly for 15 minutes without lifting lid.
Serve at once.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Refrigerate overnight. Cut center out of pumpernickel bread.
Fill center with dip.
Cut leftover bread into cubes.
Set around loaf for dipping.

title: no-fat peach-lemon salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Chill until slightly thickened.
In blender, blend until smooth the cream cheese, peaches and liquid and lemon juice.
Stir cheese-peach mixture into gelatin.
Pour into a large mold (grease lightly with Pam or mayonnaise).
Serves 12.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Stir together strawberries and 1/4 cup sugar; set aside.

title: homemade bisquick
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cut in shortening to a fine consistency with a pastry blender.
Store in container or refrigerate for longer time.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Core and shred zucchini.
Measure 10 cups.
Shred onion. Measure 4 cups.
Soak overnight, covered with water and salt. Drain and rinse thoroughly.
Put in large pot.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 30 minutes.
Put in pint jars.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: marie and dot's crumb apple cake(in honor of single g)
directions: To make filling:
Peel and slice apples.
Cook with the 1/2 cup sugar, the water and lemon until tender, but not mushy.
Drain and cool.
Remove lemon.

title: green beans with cherry tomatoes
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine beans and liquid with bacon and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Remove bacon slices and drain.
Melt butter in medium skillet; stir in sugar, garlic salt, seasoned salt, pepper and basil.
Add tomatoes and stir gently, cooking just until soft.
Pour tomatoes and sauce over green beans; toss gently.
Transfer to serving bowl and garnish with fresh basil, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: diet salad
directions: Mix together and set.

title: fruit salad
directions: Save all juice.
Let set, then add topping.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Break pretzels into smaller pieces.
On stove, melt the butter and margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add soup and stir well.
Add pretzels and toss to cover with mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour; toss pretzels every 15 minutes to keep from burning.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti and cheese
directions: Cook hen until tender; debone.
Saute celery, onion and bell pepper until tender.
Cook spaghetti in the chicken broth; drain. Mix all together.
Add the tomato and mushroom soups.
Cut up cheese into the mixture.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Serves a lot of people.

title: egg noodles for pasta
directions: Make a well in center of flour; add egg yolks, egg and salt. Mix thoroughly.
Mix in water 1 tablespoon at a time, until dough is stiff but easy to roll.
Divide dough in four equal parts, roll dough one part at a time unto paper thin rectangles on well floured board.
Cut in strips for narrow noodles.
Put on towel until dry, about 2 hours.
Use as needed.
Freeze what you don't use.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix by directions.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut over melted margarine. Pour prepared cake mix over mixture.
Melt 1 stick margarine and the cream cheese in microwave.
Stir together and add the 10x sugar and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour over cake mix. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Turn cake out upside-down as soon as taken from oven.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Add milk gradually. Cook over low heat until slightly thickened, stirring constantly. Add cheese; cook until cheese melts.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Remove crusts from bread; soak in milk until soft.
Add beef, breaking it up in small pieces.
Squeeze out excess milk from bread and lightly mix with ground beef until absorbed.
Add seasonings and shape into a large round (about 1-inch thick) or 2 smaller individual rounds.
Preheat broiler.
Place meat on oiled broiler pan.
Cook 4 inches from heat on one side for 5 minutes, then turn and sprinkle on bacon and broil another 4 to 5 minutes. Add more time for well-done meat.

title: ida's golden biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing with fork thoroughly.
Turn out onto pastry board; knead 8 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thick; cut to size you want.
Bake in a 400° oven until golden brown.
Makes about one dozen biscuits.

title: clam canapes
directions: Drain clams; reserve liquid.
Melt butter and saute onions. Blend in flour, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Stir in clam juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add minced clams; blend.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar. Add remaining ingredients slowly.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased loaf pan. Allow to cool before cutting.

title: mashed potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir lightly to mix.
Serve warm or cold.
May also be packed into molds, chilled and unmolded before serving.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake uncovered 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown on top.

title: crescent cheese breadsticks
directions: Combine cornflake crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and seasonings.
Set aside.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles. Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up, starting at shortest side of triangle and roll tightly to opposite end.
Roll to stretch each into a stick about 6 inches long.
Roll sticks in butter.
Coat with crumb mixture.
Place on ungreased pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat in eggs thoroughly.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add alternately with bananas, dates and nuts to shortening mixture.
Mix well and pour into 2 well greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients except red and green peppers.
Cut lengthwise.
Fill with mixture.
Put into a baking dish.
Bake for 50 minutes at 375°.
Remove cover.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli and chicken
directions: Mix mayo, lemon juice, sour cream and soups.
Then mix well with other ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.

title: smoky chinese chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in a cooking bag.
Rinse chicken and remove any giblets and organs.
Place chicken in cooking bag and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Turn at least once.
Place chicken in the bag in a glass baking dish.
Cut 4 to 6 slits in the top of the bag.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours depending on the size of the chicken.
Serve hot or cold.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix together and make into meatballs.
Put meatballs into frypan and brown on all sides.
Add the tomato soup and equal amounts of water.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.

title: fat-free carrot apple muffins
directions: Process ingredients in a food processor or you may mix by hand until well blended. Then add 1/2 cup raisins and 1/2 cup crushed and drained pineapple.
Bake in muffin tins at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: gayle baked country ham
directions: Soak ham overnight in cold water to cover.
In later afternoon, drain ham.
Place in roasting pan, skin side up.
Add 5 cups water; cover tightly.
(Put note on oven door, "Not to open until next morning.")
Place ham in cold oven; set temperature at 500°.
As soon as oven reaches 500°, bake for 10 minutes.
Turn off heat; leave 3 hours.
Again, turn on oven to 500°.
When oven reaches 500°, bake for 10 minutes.
Turn off heat; let it set overnight without opening oven door.

title: oatmeal whole wheat bread(makes 2 large loaves)
directions: Add oatmeal to water; cook for 2 minutes.
Add lard, milk, molasses and salt.
Cool until just warm or lukewarm.
Add yeast; let stand for 5 minutes.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour; mix well. Turn out on board and knead, sprinkling flour as necessary to keep it from sticking.
Knead at least 10 minutes.
Put in greased bowl; let rise until double.
Form into loaves; put in greased pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 40 minutes.
I usually throw in a little bran and wheat germ, too, about 1/4 cup of each.

title: orange snowballs
directions: Mix crumbs, melted margarine, 1 cup sugar and orange juice. Shape into balls.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: roman holiday bake
directions: Brown hamburger and cook sausage, onion and oregano until done.
Drain fat.
Add soups and water.
Cook noodles.
In baking dish, combine noodles and soup mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir top with Mozzarella cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: pear conserve
directions: Put fruits through food chopper on processor.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Heat to boiling stirring continuously.
Simmer at low boil for 30 minutes.
Add lemon juice from the 1 lemon.
Put in jars.
Use as an accompaniment to meats or mix with cream cheese and nuts for a delicious sandwich spread.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Melt butter in skillet and cook onions and artichokes 5 minutes or until soft.
Cook spinach according to directions and drain.
Mix spinach, onions, artichokes and cream cheese in a casserole dish.

title: vegetable soup casserole(microwave)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Place in Radarange oven; cook 7 minutes.
Stir well after 4 minutes.
Add margarine and blend well.
Return to Radarange oven and cook 2 minutes or until peanuts are golden brown.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto greased cookie sheet and let cool.
When cool, break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: pecan treats
directions: In bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass baking pan, line up graham crackers, all going the same way for easier cutting.
Bring light brown sugar and butter or margarine to boiling.
Add chopped pecans and bring again to a boil.
Remove from heat and spread over the graham crackers.
Bake in 400° oven for 5 minutes. Delicious!

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Crush saltines into a casserole dish.
Top crackers with asparagus.
Mix mushroom soup with skimmed milk.
Pour over asparagus.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: cajun chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
When chicken is finished, take out of broth; set aside to cool.
Skin and debone. Measure broth and add enough canned broth or chicken bouillons to measure 8 cups of liquid.
Turn broth on to boil.
Add chopped carrots, onion and celery.
Cut up chicken and add to broth.
Then add green peas and 1 to 2 teaspoons Creole seasoning to taste. Break angel hair into small pieces to make about 2 cups.
Add to broth and when it is done, enjoy the soup.

title: peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and baking soda; blend well.
Add peanuts and chips.
Mix just until blended.

title: beef and sherry
directions: Bake at 300° for 4 hours, or bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Also good in crock-pot.
Serve hot over hot noodles or rice.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Pat in spring form pan.
Bake 350° for 8 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and Crisco together until size of small peas.
Add salt.
Gradually add water to form small ball.
Roll out on floured board.
Make 1 inch larger than pie plate.
Put in pie plate and flute up edges.
Punch holes in pie dough with fork before baking.
Bake until golden color at 350°.

title: meatballs barbecued
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mold into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put into crock-pot with 1 can tomato soup and barbecue sauce to cover meatballs.
Cook 1 hour longer.
Can also be made into meat loaf.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix shortening, margarine, sugars, egg, almond extract and vanilla thoroughly. Mix flour and salt; stir into shortening mixture slowly. After mixing thoroughly, divide dough in half. Add red food coloring to 1 of the halves of dough. Mix to evenly distribute color.

title: fruit salad
directions: Add a drop of red food coloring.
Mix in order listed and chill before serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together white and brown sugar and flour.
Break eggs into mixture.
Add vanilla and milk.
Add melted butter.
Mix well. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes in unbaked pie shell.

title: christmas salad
directions: In top of double boiler, put water and jello, then add cut up cream cheese and marshmallows.
When they all melt, take off stove and add Miracle Whip, pineapple and pecans and fold in whipped cream.
Let congeal.

title: guacamole ring
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over cold water; let stand for 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice, salt, garlic powder and hot pepper sauce.
In large bowl, use wire whip or beater.
Combine gelatin mixture with avocados; stir in onion. Pour into a 5-cup ring mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Serve as an appetizer salad or cracker spread.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix sugar, flour, butter, eggs and milk.
Add vanilla and chopped pecans.
Pour into 2 pie crusts and bake in 350° oven for approximately 3 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Take 1 baked pie shell and fill with berries (fresh or frozen).
In saucepan, add sugar, cornstarch, water and raspberry jello. Bring to a boil until thickened.
Pour over berries.
Chill and serve.

title: cut glass candies
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Bring to boiling.
Cook to hard crack stage (290°).
Add coloring and flavoring.
Mix. Pour into pan.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: easy pineapple cream pie
directions: Combine instant pudding with the sour cream.
Add can of crushed pineapple (including juice).
Blend thoroughly.
Put mixture in crust.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Before serving, cover top with whipped topping or whipped cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cocktail chicken wings(microwave)
directions: Cut off and discard wing tips and excess skin.
Cut wings in half at joint.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over wings.
Marinate 4 to 5 hours in refrigerator, stirring twice.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Cut oranges and lemons into wedges (you do not have to remove skins or seeds).
Bring all ingredients except sugar to a boil. Simmer about 30 minutes or until cranberries are exploded.
Strain and throw pulp away.
Add sugar gradually to taste and gently reheat.

title: carrot cake supreme
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour with soda and cinnamon. Add to egg mixture.
Fold in carrots and pecans.
Place in three 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Blend powdered sugar, cheese and vanilla.
Spread between layers.
Yield: 26 servings.

title: cherry apple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in orange juice. Refrigerate until slightly set, then stir in apple and banana. Chill until firmly set.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and pour both soup and broth over.
Mix flour, butter and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken soup

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving size pieces.
Place in single layer in 9 x 13-inch pan which has been sprayed with Pam.
In a medium bowl, combine cranberries, Catalina dressing and soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: corn pie
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 325° in a 9-inch pie plate.

title: pizza
directions: Let mom and dad help you.
Take out the stuff you need.
Put all the stuff on the crust.
Put it in the oven, and put it on something low.
Let it set awhile.
Take it out of the oven and eat it.
Put the dishes in the sink.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Place chicken breasts, meaty side down, on sheet of tinfoil. Place pat of margarine on each.
Combine lemon juice, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce and pour soy sauce mixture over.
Wrap tightly.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until tender.
If using more chicken, wrap in twos.
This freezes well in the same foil it was baked in.

title: mint brownies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in greased jelly roll pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, strawberries and Eagle Brand milk well.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Make 3 holes.
In first hole put melted shortening, second hole the vanilla and in the third hole put vinegar.
Pour cold water over all.
Mix well and bake in moderate oven.
Do not use white vinegar.

title: french crunch peach pie
directions: Use single crust pastry.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain until completely dry.
Combine with remaining ingredients except bread and mix well.
Cut out center of bread, leaving a "bowl".
Spoon dip into bread.
Cut remaining bread into chunks.
Arrange on a tray with party toothpicks and use to dip.
May also be used with chips and veggie sticks.

title: deep fried shrimp
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Soak shrimp in sauce for 1 to 2 hours.
Flour and deep fry in oil.

title: hooligan's pancakes
directions: Mix flour, milk, eggs and salt together.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven while it is preheating.
Pour all ingredients into the melted butter pan and bake for 25 minutes.
Serve with your favorite syrup or jams.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except rhubarb and pie shell.
Pour into pie shell.
Place rhubarb on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: very veggie beef stew
directions: Stew beef until tender.
Add raw vegetables and cook until tender.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low heat for 30 minutes to one hour.
You may substitute left over roast for stew meat if desired.
You may also add any other left over vegetables you desire.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs for at least 30 minutes on medium heat.
Peel eggs after cooling, then cut in halves.
Place on platter or dish the egg whites.
Place yolks in bowl and mash, then add your ingredients.
Mix well, then spoon into egg whites and serve.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and onions and drain well.
Add sauce and mushrooms to meat and simmer well.

Layer two times in buttered crock-pot the cooked noodles, meat sauce, cheese and pepperoni. Cook in crock-pot on low and serve when cheese is melted or you may cook on high for approximately 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in oven until cheese is melted.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together sugar, butter and milk in a heavy saucepan (5-quart).
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour on a greased pan.

title: mushroom country style steak
directions: Combine salt, pepper and flour; roll steak in mixture.
Brown in butter.
Meanwhile, heat soup and water in saucepan.
Remove steak to baking dish.
Reserve excess butter and steak drippings in pan.
Pour mushroom soup in frying pan with drippings and stir. Pour this over steak and cover.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: mary's egg kisses
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in large bowl until foamy. Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto large brown paper bags placed on cookie sheets.
(Do not grease bag.)
Cook for 1 hour at 275°. Turn off oven and don't open door until cool.
Works best if let sit in oven overnight.

title: pistachio-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove stems from mushrooms; finely chop stems.
In a skillet, saute stems and onion in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add all other ingredients except remaining butter and mix well.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Place stuffed mushrooms on an ungreased baking sheet.
Melt remaining 3 tablespoons butter and drizzle over mushrooms.
Bake for 5 minutes or until hot.
Enjoy!!

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add onions and cook until transparent. Add the next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Cover and bake 1/2 hour at 350° (9 x 13-inch baking pan).
Remove cover.
Spread with 1 large can Chinese noodles and 1 can sliced cashew nuts.
Bake 10 minutes, uncovered.
Mixture freezes well before baking.
I add some grated ginger root.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in oblong dish.
Heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour and salt mixture.
Roll into ball as you sprinkle milk over dough. Roll into oblong shape about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread apples over dough and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up like jelly roll and seal edges by dipping fingers in water and pinching together.
Slice with sharp knife about 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place cut side up in dish in the melted butter.
Pour sugar and water mixture over this (be sure to use it all).
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm or with ice cream.
Good!

title: peaches for fried pies
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
Cook until thickened.
Cook approximately 2 hours constantly.
Can and seal.

title: zippy tom-tom salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender container.
Press button 6 for 10 seconds.
Yield:

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and bake at 325° until hot.
May be heated in microwave.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in medium bowl with wooden spoon until creamy and well blended.
Mix flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown in a 350° oven.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder, 1 teaspoon of salt and 1 1/2 teaspoons of sugar, if desired.
Add milk and oil with eggs to dry mixture.
Mix thoroughly and pour into heavily-greased baking pan.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.
Cool and crumble. Combine with remaining ingredients and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk in large, heavy saucepan.
Bring to full, rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Add peanut butter until melted.
Continue boiling over medium heat for 4 minutes. Take off heat; stir in Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: skillet sausage and cabbage
directions: Saute sausage in large heavy skillet over medium heat until browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Add onion and bell pepper to skillet and saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook, stirring often, 8 minutes.
Add sausage, chicken broth and remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cabbage and wieners
directions: Brown cabbage in fat.
Mix together remaining ingredients; add to cabbage.
Place 8 wieners on top of cabbage.
Cover pan; heat for 20 to 30 minutes on low, until wieners are hot.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Remove macaroni from heat.
Wash in cold water.
Beat together the evaporated milk, eggs, butter, sugar and salt.
Pour mixture over macaroni.
Place in an ovenproof casserole container.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and top is golden brown.
Um um good!

title: toffee thins
directions: Line a baking pan with graham crackers (pan needs to be at least 2 inches deep).
Usually takes two 9 x 13 x 2-inch pans. Sprinkle chopped nuts on each graham cracker.
Boil butter and brown sugar for 2 minutes, then spoon over crackers.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let sit for a few minutes, then remove from pans and spread on wax paper.

title: marinated beans
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and black pepper.
Pour over remaining ingredients and let set overnight.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Roll 8 beans in 1/2 slice of bacon; secure with toothpick. There will be enough bundles to fill an 11 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Melt butter; stir in sugar and spices.
Pour over bundles. Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes more.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs in serving pieces.
Brown slowly in skillet. Put in baking dish or pan.
Pour fat from skillet.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion.
Cook until brown.
Add next 9 ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes.
Set oven to 350°.
Pour sauce over ribs. Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chunky quiche
directions: *May substitute fresh mushrooms and onions sauteed in butter and 1 small can chicken for soup and cream of mushroom soup.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch pan. Mix all other ingredients. Take can of fruit and pour off half of the juice, then pour fruit over batter and bake.
Bake at 325° until golden.

title: red earth cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix together cocoa, coffee, red food coloring and vanilla.
Stir into mixture.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add flour and buttermilk to mixture alternately.
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Ice with your favorite frosting.
You can use a 9 x 12-inch sheet cake pan.

title: better than robert redford
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, butter, nuts and 1/4 cup Oreo cookies together.
Pat into flat crust in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cut corn off the cob.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add milk, sugar and salt.
Stir in corn and melted butter.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 375° until set and brown.
(I use 2 cans of corn, drained, if I don't have fresh corn.)

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Mix Coke and juice from cherries and bring to boil.
Add jello and let cool.
Mix cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Add to cooled jello.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and syrup, then salt and vanilla.
Place the pecans in
the bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Add the filling. Bake slowly in a moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
The nuts will rise to the top of the pie filling and form a crusted layer.

title: stew by oven
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 5 to 6 hours at 300°. Serve with biscuits or rolls.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place meat in bottom of casserole. Cover with celery, carrots and potatoes. Sprinkle tapioca, salt, pepper and sugar on top. Add sliced onion and pour V-8 juice and wine over all. Cover and bake at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Defrost broccoli; cook and drain.
Add can of soup
and mix. Add mayonnaise and broken cheese slices.
Mix up good.
Pour into pan; top with shredded American cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until bubbling and brown on top.
Let settle 15 minutes before serving.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, butter, scallions and 1 cup cheese in
a lightly greased deep 3-quart casserole.
Gently stir in potatoes, salt and pepper.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and the bread crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350°
oven for 30 minutes (longer if refrigerated).
Makes 10 servings.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream the confectioners sugar, oleo or butter, milk and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
(Use powdered sugar to drop hands into as you roll the balls.)
Melt the chocolate and paraffin over low heat.
Dip balls into this mixture, one piece at a time, holding each with a toothpick.
Drop on wax paper.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix well;
roll out on floured board and cut in squares.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon; saute onion in bacon fat.
Drain green beans; put in casserole. Toss in crumbled bacon, sauteed onion, salt, pepper and grated Parmesan cheese with tomato wedges.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pickled asparagus
directions: Blanch asparagus for 2 minutes.
Cool and put into hot pint jars.
Add 1 teaspoon dill, 1/8 teaspoon black pepper (you can add a little red if desired) and 1/2 clove garlic to each jar.
Heat the water, vinegar, sugar and salt; cover with asparagus.
Seal and process for 10 minutes.

title: artichoke dressing
directions: In a large pot, put about 6 ounces of olive oil.
Chop celery and garlic and add to olive oil.
Cook until clear.
Add artichoke hearts, saving a little of the liquid from the artichoke can.
Add bread crumbs a little at a time until fairly stiff.
Add the extra olive oil and water if needed.
Put 1 cup cheese in mixture and slowly cook on a low fire for 1/2 hour.
Salt and pepper to taste (be careful with the salt as the cheese is salty also).
Place dressing in casserole dish and cover with the rest of the cheese. Slice lemon on top of dressing.
Bake for about 1/2 hour on a low setting.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until thick as egg whites.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Chill overnight.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients except Jell-O.
Cook all ingredients, except
Jell-O until it is thick. Set off heat, then add Jell-O. Cool,
then
brown	pie
shell.
Cool, then add fresh cleaned strawberries
in
baked
pie
shell.
Cover
with pie filling. Let
cool in refrigerator for 2 hours. Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Set in fridge for 2 hours.
Make small balls; fry in butter.

title: tomato slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate, covered, overnight before serving.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients; drop by tablespoons onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil; cool.
Drain vegetables and mix.
Pour the cooled mixture over the vegetables and allow to marinate overnight.
Will keep for a long time.
The longer it marinates, the better it tastes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Layer pieces of chicken, onion and Doritos chips in dish. Heat all liquid ingredients together in a saucepan.
Sprinkle cheese over layered ingredients.
Pour liquid ingredients over this and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
This will serve at least 4 people.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Wrap breasts with bacon.
Cover bottom of greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan with chipped beef.
Arrange breasts over beef.
Combine soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: roasted garlic and chicken salad
directions: Combine
peppers
and
garlic in a shiny pan; toss with rosemary,
salt,
pepper
and
tablespoon oil.
Spread in a single
layer.
Place chicken in pan with vegetables.
Bake at 400°
for
minutes.
Stir occasionally or until vegetables and chicken
are
done.
Transfer
red pepper and garlic to a bowl. Let
chicken
stand
until
cool enough to handle.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips.
Combine spinach, onion, roasted pepper, roasted
garlic and chicken in a large bowl.
Combine soy
sauce, vinegar and remaining 3 tablespoons oil in a jar. Cover
and shake.
Drizzle over salad and toss gently.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Soften margarine in microwave for about 30 seconds at power level 5.
Cream margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs in large bowl. Stir in flour and blend in chips.
Spread into greased 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan and bake at 375° for 20-25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares to serve.

title: carrot bars(nutritious spicy bars with a brown butter frosting.)
directions: Cream the sugar, oil and eggs until well blended.
Stir in flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Fold in grated carrots and nuts. Pour into lightly greased and lightly floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven until tests done with a toothpick for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost while warm with Brown Butter Frosting.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine oranges, jello (powder), whipped topping, and cottage cheese.
Mix gently.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.
Serve chilled.

title: barbecue
directions: Wash roast; season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Place in crock-pot with 1/2 cup of water.
Place sliced onion on top and cook overnight on low setting.
Next morning, discard onion. Remove roast and wash pot.
Pull meat apart; discard bone and fat. Put shredded meat back into crock-pot; add barbecue sauce and minced onion.
Cook for 3 or 4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: baked fish
directions: Mix.
Put on both sides fish.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until fish are golden brown.

title: white frosting
directions: Heat syrup just until hot.
Add sugar.
To this, add egg whites, beaten stiff and pinch of salt.
Beat all together until fluffy.
Add vanilla.

title: salmon croquettes or patties
directions: Mix all together and shape into patties or croquette shape. Pan-fry or bake in oven.

title: spinach bread
directions: Melt butter and saute onion, garlic and cheese.
Melt.
Defrost spinach and add.
Cook until melted and heated well.
Cut bread into and spread evenly on loaves.
Bake in oven until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash; boil 3 minutes.
Drain.
Chop onion and celery. Cook in margarine until soft.
Mix soup, Miracle Whip, sour cream, milk, mushrooms and beaten eggs with cornbread stuffing mix and then add squash.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.
This may be frozen.

title: company casserole
directions: Mix until smooth cream cheese, evaporated milk, lemon juice, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with cooked noodles. In 10-inch skillet, cook onions, peppers, butter, tomato sauce and ketchup.
Cook over medium heat 8 minutes until mixture thickens. Spread over noodles.
Bake in 375° oven 10 minutes until hot. Garnish with little meatballs.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: all day stew
directions: Peel and chunk all vegetables.
Put all ingredients (except beans) in a Dutch oven or big covered roasting pan.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours. About 1/2 hour before serving, add the beans.
No peeking before then.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Saute chilies and season; cook 10 minutes.
Add sour cream. Top with cheese and bake until bubbly.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick.
Add strawberry Jell-O. Pour over fresh strawberries in a cooked pie crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: karen's vegetable casserole
directions: Combine undiluted soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and half of French-fried onion rings.
Mix in thawed and drained vegetables in a casserole bowl.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes (longer if still cold).
Then add remaining onions and cheese and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes more.

title: easy mexican rice
directions: *If you prefer brown rice, increase liquids by 1/2 cup each.

title: rotel dip
directions: Dump tomatoes (juice included) in top of double boiler.
Add cubed cheese and heat until melted stirring constantly.
Brown sausage and drain; add to hot cheese.
Add mushrooms.
Can be kept hot or warm on a hot plate or chafing dish.
Serve with chips.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar, syrup and cornstarch. Cook until thickened and clear. Add Jell-O and red food coloring. Let cool. Spread small amount in pie crust. Fill with strawberries and pour the rest of the filling over the strawberries. When cool, top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: potato cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix grated potatoes and chopped onion in bowl.
Stir in egg whites and mix well.
Add bread crumbs and pepper and mix together.
Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add 1/4 cup of mixture into skillet and flatten into a round rectangle.
Lightly brown pancakes on each side (if they are not cooked enough on the first side before turning they will fall apart).
Transfer to a baking sheet which has been sprayed with vegetable spray.
Bake pancakes stacked on each other for about 15 minutes.
Turn once and bake another 10 minutes.
If you prefer potato cakes crispier, use enough baking sheets to have a single layer of potato cakes.
Reduce baking time to 8 to 10 minutes on each side.
Makes 12 (2 pancake) servings.

title: sweet pickle strips
directions: Use large cucumbers; peel, remove seeds and cut into long strips.
Mix water and lime.
Soak cucumber strips in mixture for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Wash several times; soak in ice water for about 2 hours.
Drain well.
Cook vinegar, sugar, salt and spices for 20 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers strips; let soak overnight.
Cook for 30 minutes; pack in jars.
A little red, green or yellow food coloring may be added.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix well and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Separate leaves of cabbage by steaming in a large pot with water covering half the cabbage.
Brown onion and garlic.
Mix hamburger, sausage, salt, pepper and rice until well blended.
Add browned mixture and mix until blended.
Take a few spoonfuls of meat mixture and put in cabbage leaves to wrap.
Proceed until all of the meat mixture is used.
Place any remaining cabbage leaves on the bottom of the pot in the water where the cabbage was steamed.
Put cabbage rolls in layers on top of leaves. Pour tomatoes or soup on top.
Heat until boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer on low for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lori's sweet pickles
directions: Drain juice off of pickles; rinse and slice.
Mix water, seeds, vinegar, sugar and cinnamon stick.
Pour over pickles and let stand about a week, stirring every day.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into small amounts (4 to 5).
Roll out on floured surface.
Fill circles with favorite filling.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 5 pies.

title: fettuccine with garlic basil cream sauce
directions: Heat oil in a small skillet over low heat.
Add garlic; cook until golden, turning cloves over as they color, 6 minutes.
Add basil; cook 10 seconds.
Transfer to food processor; add pepper. Whirl until creamy.
Meanwhile, cook fettuccine in a large pot of boiling water, according to package directions.
Drain.
Add to bowl with yogurt sauce.
Toss to mix.

title: strawberry bavarian
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with lemon juice. Fold in Cool Whip. Last, add the drained strawberries. Break the cake into chunks after removing all the brown part.
Pour mixture over the cake and put into a large Pyrex casserole.
(No need to line the casserole.)

title: old fashion corn meal mush
directions: Sprinkle corn meal gradually into boiling salted water, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks and buttermilk.
Fold in sifted flour, baking powder, soda and spices.
Mix well.
Add jam, raisins, coconut and pecans. Whip egg whites until firm; fold into batter.
Divide batter equally into 3 (9-inch) layer pans that have been greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until well done. Spread between layers and top with your favorite caramel frosting.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup juice.
Combine with juice in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir in apples and coat well.
Put in pie crust.
Sprinkle with spice and top with remaining crust.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.

title: cinnamon raisin bars
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients, then add all other ingredients. Pour into 9 inch x 13 inch greased
and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.

title: oven fries
directions: Scrub potatoes well; peel if desired.
Slice in 1/4-inch rounds.
Spray a baking sheet with butter flavored vegetable spray.
Place potatoes on sheet in single layers and spray with vegetable spray; sprinkle with salt, seasoned salt or chili powder.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 325° or until golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Blend together cream cheese and cottage cheese.
Spread on platter.
Top with green pepper, minced onion and tomatoes. Sprinkle on taco seasoning.
Top with Cheddar cheese and taco cheese.
Finish with black olives.
Sprinkle on more taco seasoning.

title: harvard beets
directions: Pour off almost 3/4 cup juice; add vinegar.
Mix with sugar, flour and salt and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Pour beets into mixture until hot through.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs and jam.
Sift soda, flour and spices together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture. Add pecans and raisins. Pour in angel food cake pan which has been buttered and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pudding frosting
directions: Cook milk and cornstarch until thick and set aside.
Mix well, oleo, Crisco, sugar and vanilla.
Add, while mixing, cornstarch mixture, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat well between spoonfuls. Frost cake.
Chill to set in fridge.

title: reese's peanut butter cup bars
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Press into a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
In a pan, melt chips and spread on top.
Refrigerate.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift
flour,
sugar
and soda together.
Cut in Crisco. Add yeast and buttermilk.
Knead well.
Roll out dough and cut out biscuits.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: beef roast
directions: Flour roast on all sides.
Put oil in skillet which has been reheated.
Brown roast on all sides.
Remove and put in roasting pan.
Add water and onion soup mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Put grated cheese on spaghetti at each serving melted in microwave.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning in refried beans.
Layer ingredients on a large platter in the order listed.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Garnish with greens or nasturtiums.
Dip with chips.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken about 1/2 hour.
Slice chicken into bite size pieces.
Layer greased baking dish with cooked broccoli.
Cover with chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice. Cover chicken with this mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, flour and salt.
Add boiling water and cook until thick.
Add butter, cream and vanilla, stirring until melts.
Serve over Woodford pudding, bread pudding, etc.

title: raw vegetable marinade
directions: Slice raw vegetables (carrots, onions, peppers and zucchini); put in marinade.
Shake or stir.
Let stand for a few hours before serving.
Will keep up to two weeks in refrigerator.

title: tina white's cheese pie
directions: Bake pie crust according to package directions and cool.
Beat cream cheese with confectioners sugar and vanilla using an electric beater.
In a separate bowl beat heavy cream until thick. By hand fold whipped cream into cheese mixture until well mixed. Pour onto cooled crust.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Crush cereal slightly.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Blend shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Stir in thawed orange juice, milk and nuts.
Add sifted dry ingredients, stirring only until combined.
Fold in cereal. Spread in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.
Cool before slicing.

title: gazpacho with crab or lobster surimi
directions: Blend in processor or blender until pureed.
Put in a bowl. Stir in crab or Surimi.
Serve chilled with crusty bread.

title: sweet crunchy dills
directions: Drain pickles.
Slice into 1/2-inch.
Alternate layers of pickles, sugar and hot sauce.
Let stand 1 day.
Turn second day. Turn over third day.
On 4th day, they are ready to eat.
They will make their own juice.

title: kamaboko cole slaw
directions: Chop kamaboko, cabbage and green onions.
Add garlic-sesame sticks.
Just before serving, add mayonnaise and mix.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Melt margarine with baking cocoa in saucepan; stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Add pecans; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Do not store in refrigerator.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add next flour, baking soda and baking powder; mix.
Add can of drained (save juice) pineapple, vanilla and chopped nuts; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375° until lightly browned.
While still warm drizzle with thick icing of powdered sugar and the pineapple juice.
Makes a soft, moist cookie.
Makes a large batch.

title: new england pumpkin casserole
directions: Mix pumpkin, white sauce, ham and 1 cup cheese.
Place half of mixture in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with sliced eggs.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Sprinkle with coarsely crumbled crackers, remaining cheese and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine sugar.
Add flour, mixing well.
Add melted butter and milk.
Beat until well blended. Add coconut.
Pour into two greased 9-inch pie plates.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes until golden brown on top.

title: country chicken 'n biscuits
directions: In a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine the first 4 ingredients and 1 cup cheese.
Blend soup and 3/4 cup milk; pour over casserole.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the cream cheese, 1 egg, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread on bottom of unbaked pie shell. Beat 3 eggs until well mixed, but not foamy. Add rest and pour over cream cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: bakewell tart
directions: Line a 7 to 8-inch pie or tart pan with pastry.
Spread jam on bottom of pastry.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add egg, almonds and baking powder.
Spread almond mixture on top of jam. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken normandy(4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute chicken in the butter until half done.
Place the apples in a casserole dish.
Top with the chicken pieces.
Swirl the calvados in the pan and pour over chicken. Cover and bake in oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a food processor, process 1/4 cup almonds with the sugar until finely ground.
Add the butter and process until incorporated.
Add egg white and vanilla and almond extracts; pulse until combined.
Add baking powder and salt; pulse until blended.
Add the flour and process until incorporated. Transfer the dough to a work surface and divide it into 8 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into a ball and arrange about 3 inches apart in a large baking sheet.
Lightly flatten the balls into 2-inch rounds.
Decorate each cookie by pressing slivered almonds into the dough in a star pattern.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with mayonnaise, cocktail sauce and mustard. Stir in the crab meat and celery. Cover and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Cream well.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to warm milk, then potato mixture.
Add flour to make stiff dough.
Put on board and knead well.
Put in large bowl; let rise double in bulk.
Knead lightly.
Rub top with melted butter.
Place in refrigerator about 1 1/2 hours.
Shape in rolls and let rise until double in size. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: golden pear salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients; spoon into pear halves. Arrange on lettuce.
Yields 2 servings.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo for 3 minutes.
Add beef and brown.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan layer tomato, meat sauce and uncooked noodles.
Make sure noodles are well
covered with sauce. Top with cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set for 10 to 15 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: squash relish
directions: Put all vegetables in a dishpan and sprinkle with salt.
Cover with towel and let set 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Drain.

title: scallops provencale(makes 4 servings)
directions: Rinse and dry scallops.
Combine salt, pepper and flour in large dish.
Roll scallops in flour mixture until completely coated.
Heat oil in skillet; add coated scallops and garlic to heated oil and saute until golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until thoroughly heated.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well, pour into casserole and cover with topping.

title: german kraut dinner
directions: In a bag add brown sugar, caraway seed, pepper and ground cloves.

title: pastry with vinegar
directions: Measure vinegar in milk.
Add salt to measured flour.
Cut in shortening and milk.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large pan, heat olive oil on medium heat.
Add celery and onion and cook until limp.
Turn heat to high and add ground chuck.
Cook quickly until browned.
Take off heat and add tomatoes (with the juice).
Cut the tomatoes up and then add paste and tomato sauce.
Stir until blended.
Add spices; stir.
Cook slowly for about 8 hours.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in boiler and cook until thick. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, then add cake mix over top evenly. Spread margarine over cake evenly.
Add pecans and bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: jen's raspberry coffee cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar, cut in butter.
Reserve 1 cup of the crumbs.
To the remaining crumbs add: egg, sour cream, salt, baking soda, baking powder and almond extract.
Mix well.
Spread into a 10 inch spring form baking pan.
Run batter slightly up the sides of the pan.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cake mix and egg yolks.
Blend in enough milk to mix well.
Add remaining milk; cook until thick.
Add butter, then coconut and pour into baked crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: squash souffle
directions: Melt butter. Add flour and mix well. Add eggs and milk.
Cook until thick. Add squash and cheese.
Put in casserole dish lined with bread crumbs. Cover and bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 400° or until brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground steak with garlic powder, salt and pepper. Drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Place in a large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: banana-chip-nut bread
directions: Cream the oil and sugar together in mixing bowl.
Beat the eggs until light and add to the mixture.
Thoroughly mash the bananas and fold into the oil, sugar and egg mixture.
Add the flour and baking soda.
Stir in the cherry juice, cherries, chips and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: hamburger and tater tots
directions: Brown ground beef and onion lightly.
Season with salt.
Drain off grease.
Add mushroom soup and 1/2 soup can of water.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Place Tater Tots on top of beef mixture.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jellied waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and vinegar.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in apples, celery, nuts and mayonnaise.
Pour into a 4 cup mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold.
Serve with crisp greens and mayonnaise, if desired.
Makes about 3 cups or 6 servings.

title: onion patties
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, adding a little more if needed to make a thick batter.
Mix in onion.
Heat oil in a deep-fat fryer to 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoons into oil and fry to a golden brown; turn and brown other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.
Great with beans.

title: holiday fruit balls
directions: Combine margarine, marshmallows, and milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Combine cracker crumbs, fruit, and nuts in a large mixing bowl.
Add milk mixture, stirring until well mixed.
Form into 1 1/2 inch balls and roll in coconut.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage and salt in water for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Put a layer of cabbage in greased casserole; cover with one-half can of soup and 3 slices of cheese.
Repeat layer.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with crumbs and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese puffies
directions: Put flour in food processor bowl with knife.
Add butter (cut in pieces).
Add cayenne.
Add cheese.
Work off/on until blended. Roll into little balls.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream Crisco in mixer and add sugar gradually; cream well together.

title: potato supreme
directions: Defrost hash browns and combine in large bowl with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Add salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into buttered 3-quart casserole. Mix remaining butter with corn flakes and sprinkle over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Filling: Cook the chopped dates, sugar and water to a boil. Cool. Add chopped nuts.

title: little pigs
directions: Cook pork roast until well done.
Cool and chop very fine. Set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients with chopped pork and place in crock-pot on low.
Great for parties!

title: corn pone
directions: Mix all ingredients (butter last).
Put in 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° to 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, thoroughly mix all ingredients, except chili sauce.
Place mixture in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake for 30 minutes.
Spread the chili sauce over the top of the loaf, return it to the oven and bake for an additional 30 minutes, until no pink remains in the center.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: lentils monastics
directions: Wash lentils (don't soak).
Bring to boil in kettle with water, salt and herbs.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook onion and carrot slowly in olive oil until soft, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add to lentils with parsley, tomatoes and sherry.
Cover and simmer one hour, or until lentils are tender.
When ready to serve, put 1 tablespoon (or more) grated cheese in each bowl and top with lentils.
(The olive oil is very important to this recipe, as it adds a satisfying "meaty" flavor.)
A good budget recipe.

title: minestrone
directions: Saute onion in oil in large saucepan.
Add all ingredients except macaroni and green beans.
Cook, covered, over medium-low heat for 45 minutes.
Add beans and macaroni.
Cook until macaroni is tender, about 15 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat the egg whites for top.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 2 minutes. Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: make-ahead breakfast bake
directions: Crumble sausage into skillet and brown over medium heat, stirring.
Drain off grease.
Spread bread squares in bottom of 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, greased with butter.
Spread sausage and cheese over bread.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornstarch and water in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low for 3-4 hours or until carrots are tender.
Place carrots in serving dish and keep warm reserving juices in small sauce pan.
Bring remaining juice to a boil.
Mix cornstarch and water in small bowl until blended well.
Add to juices.
Boil one minute or until thick stirring constantly.
Pour over carrots and serve.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1-inch squares.
Cover with waxed paper and pound them into thin, or use the chicken cutlets.
Dip in beaten eggs, then dip into the bread crumbs.
Spray a Teflon frying pan lightly with olive oil spray and brown the breaded chicken on both sides.
Place chicken in a baking dish; add marinara sauce and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with your favorite pasta. Enjoy.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325°, until firm.

title: strawberry sour cream mold
directions: You will
make
1/2 of the gelatin mixture, then spread sour cream.
Then top with remainder of gelatin mixture.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix as listed.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Very good plain or frosted with whipped cream or butter and cream cheese frosting.

title: onion rings
directions: Separate the onions into rings and soak in a bowl of ice water for about 2 hours.
Prepare batter by combining remaining ingredients, except oil, in a large bowl.
Add 1 1/2 cups of ice water all at once and whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before using.
Pour 2 inches oil into heavy saucepan or deep fryer.
Heat until almost smoking (375°; must be).
Place all of the onions into batter and stir to coat.
Working in batches, drop onion rings, one by one, into hot oil.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes, turning once until crisp and golden.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with salt.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and pour over crushed Ritz crackers.
Mix well and put about 1/2 in bottom of a Pyrex dish appproximately 6 x 13 x 2-inches.
Mix other ingredients together and pour on top of crackers.
Sprinkle remaining cracker mixture on top and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: velveeta cheese candy
directions: Melt cheese and oleo together in double boiler.
Combine sugar, cocoa, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well and add to cheese and oleo mixture.
Press into 2 buttered 9 x 13-inch dishes.
(Use smaller dishes if you want thicker candy.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter slowly.
Add milk.
Blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip and beat 3 minutes.
Pour into crust.
Cover and put in freezer.
Set out 30 minutes before serving.

title: molded shrimp salad
directions: Boil soup.
Add cheese and beat smooth.
Add gelatin, dissolved in cold water.
when thoroughly cold, add mayonnaise, chopped vegetables and shelled shrimp.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.
May be made in a large mold and used as an hors d'oeuvre with crackers or in individual molds for a luncheon salad.

title: crazy apple pie(serves 8)
directions: Cut margarine and cream cheese into flour to form pastry. Chill for 1 hour.
Press to fit 9-inch pie pan or if preferred, roll on lightly floured board and shape in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix salad dressing ingredients (celery seed, onion, sugar, oil, mustard, vinegar and seasonings).
Assemble torn spinach leaves, croutons, cooked, crumbled bacon and eggs (if desired). Toss with dressing just before serving.

title: nanny's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oats; let stand.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs into sugar mixture and mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.	Mix flour mixture with sugar mixture.
Add oats and beat well.
Pour into oblong pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: beef casserole 1
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Do not remove during cooking time.
Serve over rice or green noodles.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 1 1/2 sticks melted butter (save 1/2 cup for topping).
Mix and press firmly in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Beat together for 20 minutes the powdered sugar, 2 sticks butter, 2 eggs and vanilla.
Spread on top of crumbs.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease casserole dish; add apples, water and lemon juice which has been mixed with spices.
Work together sugar, salt, flour and butter until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake (at about 350°) uncovered until apples are tender.
Serve warm plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover only with water and cook vegetables until fork-tender. Add milk/cream and butter.
Bring to a boil and thicken with cornstarch/Wondra.

title: curry chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In shallow baking pan, melt margarine. Add honey, curry powder, mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir thoroughly.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach; drain and squeeze out excess moisture.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter.
Chop parsley.
Combine all and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: cheese-topped pumpkin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray or line muffin cups with paper baking cups and spray paper cups with nonstick cooking spray.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice and salt; mix well.
In small bowl, combine pumpkin, milk, oil and egg whites; blend well.
Add to dry ingredients all at once; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter evenly into spray-coated muffin cups. Press 1 cube cream cheese product into center of each muffin.
Top each with 1/2 teaspoon brown sugar.
Bake at 400° for 14 to 18 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center, but not into cream cheese, comes out clean.
Immediately remove from pan; serve warm. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 12 muffins.
Contains 170 cal.; 5 grams fat.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given and beat with rotary beater until blended. Pour into chilled pie shell. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Tie spices in a cloth.
Boil with sugar and 4 cups cold water for 10 minutes.
Then add 10 cups boiling water with tea leaves tied in a cloth.
Let steep until cold.
Remove the bags.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.
Heat for serving.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Hollow out loaf of rye bread. Cut additional rye bread into cubes.
Serve with dip.

title: kentucky moonshine
directions: Lots of water, but remember that it swells.
This is called mash.
You have to keep it at room temperature, but when you are hiding in the hills, you dig a hole underneath and set a kerosene lamp under the barrel, protected with a tin so it doesn't go up in smoke.
Let it set for 10 days, then you take a wash boiler with coils attached and cook over a good old kerosene two burner stove. This takes many hours and needs to be watched closely.
The coil is connected to a jar below and the liquid slowly drains into the jar. The first batch is called tailing and is not that pure or fit for human consumption, but some just couldn't wait.
The second boil is better, but the third is pure good stuff.
Then you sit back and enjoy every drop.
Also good as medicinal purposes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Grease and flour the bottom only of a 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
Pour prepared cake mix batter into pan and bake according to directions.
Remove cake from oven; using a large fork, poke holes in cake.
Combine condensed milk and cream of coconut; pour over warm cake.
Spread pineapple over cake.
Cool completely. Spread whipped topping over all and sprinkle with coconut.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours before serving.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: poor man's pound cake
directions: Have everything at room temperature.
Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat at high speed for 10 minutes.
Pour into tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Start oven when you put cake in oven.

title: taco salad - 6 layer
directions: Mix sliced avocados, lemon juice and salt. Set aside.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Set aside.
Mix together refried beans and set aside.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan starting with the beans, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, onions, tomatoes and top with cheese.
(Can be made the day before.)

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix sausage, cooked rice and pepper together. Take outside leaves off cabbage and cook 1 minute.
Lay cabbage leaves in bottom of casserole dish. Spoon meat mixture on leaves. Shred rest of the cabbage and put on top of meat mixture.
Top with can of tomatoes and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sue's peach dessert
directions: Mix and press into large Pyrex dish.
Bake until brown.
Cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the chicken (cut up), celery, eggs (cut up), pimento, onion and mushrooms.
Add soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Mix well.
Put in 8 x 11 inch casserole pan.
Top with the following before baking:
1 cup grated cheddar cheese, 1 1/2 cup crushed potato chips, 2/3 cup slivered almonds.

title: easter egg spread
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk until smooth in a mixing bowl.
Add seasonings and beat until blended.
Stir in eggs.
Cover and chill until firm.
Spread on crackers.
Make a sandwich filling or stuffing for tomatoes or celery sticks.

title: sauerkraut and sausage
directions: Cook sausage until brown. Remove. Cook onion and celery in sausage liquid. Place sauerkraut and cabbage in skillet. Add the cooked sausage. Cover and cook until well heated.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 150 cookies.

title: chinese ham salad
directions: In a large bowl stir together corn oil, syrup, soy sauce, ginger and pepper.
Add ham, rice, water chestnuts, green pepper, carrot and onion.
Toss to coat well.
Cover.
Chill at least one hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Cut up chicken, season with salt, garlic salt, Season-All (seasoned salt) and lemon and pepper seasoning.
Brown in small amount of Crisco.
In another pan, fry sausage.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Take chicken off bone and cut in bite-size pieces.
In grease from chicken, saute onions, garlic and okra.
If more grease is needed, use drippings from sausage.
Pour off grease and make a roux with this.
