Add all ingredients in deep pot and add water. Amount of water is determined by how thick or thin you want this to be.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Add gumbo file, if desired.
Green salad and garlic French bread make a complete meal.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown meat and onions together; drain well.
Add taco sauce mix, taco sauce, tomato sauce and beans.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Put chopped lettuce, tomatoes and shredded cheese in a large bowl.
When ready to serve, pour meat mixture over salad.
Mix.
Add Doritos and serve.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Heat applesauce.
Cream sugar and shortening and add to hot applesauce.
Blend flour, soda, salt and spices.
Toss to coat fruit and nuts.
Add all to applesauce mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of graham cracker crust.
Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thickened.
Add lemon flavoring and blueberries.
Cool slightly before putting mixture on top of cream cheese.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine soda and buttermilk and let stand for a few minutes. Cream together shortening and margarine.
Add egg yolks (which have been slightly beaten) to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk mixture alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Add coconut and pecans. For large cake, bake 45 minutes at 350°.
For sheet cake, bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: texas triple dip
directions: Prepare guacamole. Peel and mash avocados; add lemon juice, salt and 4 tablespoons picante sauce. Combine and mix well. Layer equal amounts of guacamole, sour cream and picante sauce. Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: mom's congo cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Melt shortening and add sugar.
Cool.
Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Add chips, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Spread bread in bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Add meat.
Mix eggs and 1 1/2 cups of the milk.
Mix together mustard, remaining 1/2 cup milk and the soup.
Combine the 2 liquid mixtures and pour over bread and meat.
Add cheese on top. Cover tightly with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Place in cool oven.
Turn oven to 300° and bake 1 1/2 hours or until puffy and brown.

title: crabmeat balls
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; stir well.
Stir in crabmeat and egg yolks.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Dredge balls in flour.
Pour oil to depth of 2 to 3 inches in Dutch oven or heavy saucepan.
Heat to 375°.
Fry balls in oil until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in large skillet until meat is done. Add other ingredients in a 3 qt. sauce pan; mix well. Add ground beef mixture. Heat on stove on medium heat until starts to boil, stirring to keep from sticking. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mints
directions: Cook about 15 minutes, without stirring, until a drop in cold water will crack.
Add flavoring.
Pour onto a
cold, buttered marble slab.
As it begins to cool, pull with hands and cut.

title: john's 3 minute pie dough
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt directly into a 9-inch pie pan. Mix well.
In a small glass jar, add 1/2 cup cooking oil and 2 tablespoons cold milk.
Shake well after closing lid.
Very gently, pour into pie pan with dry ingredients.
Mix together gently. As dough forms, press around the edge of pan. Add filling.

title: martha server's sausage cake
directions: Melt sugar, half and half and butter and add sugar and vanilla.
Store in a cool place.

title: ann lander's meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pat into loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips of bacon.
Pour over top 1 (8 ounce) can tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serves 6.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan and add dough.
Melt chocolate and add it to the pie.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Put pie crust on top.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger-potato casserole
directions: Brown chuck and onions.
Place in casserole; cover with vegetables and soup.
Place a layer of Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: In a large heavy pan or electric pan, brown meat. Add gravy, salt, pepper and bay leaf. Cover and cook over low heat 2 hours. Add potatoes, carrots and onion.
Cook 1 hour more or until tender. Stir occasionally.
Uncover and cook to desired consistency. Spoon off fat.
Remove bay leaf.
Garnish with parsley.

title: cornbread
directions: Melt grease in pan.
Mix cornmeal, flour, eggs and milk; pour half of melted grease on top of milk mixture.
Heat pan with shortening.
Pour in mix.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Can bake in an iron skillet.

title: "coconut cake"
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Slice in 3 or 4 layers.
Mix sugar, sour cream and vanilla flavoring together.
Add 1 1/2 packages coconut to sugar mixture.
Place filling between cake layers only. Mix remaining coconut with Cool Whip and ice sides and top of cake. Let stand overnight or several hours before serving.
Keep stored in refrigerator.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Add well beaten egg.
Add applesauce.
Sift flour once before measuring.
Use a small amount of the flour to dredge fruit and nuts.
Sift remaining flour with salt and spices.
Dissolve soda in boiling coffee.
Add this alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Add floured nuts and fruit.
Pour mixture into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Mix the sugar and melted butter together.
Pour over the crushed pretzels which have been placed in the bottom of an aluminum pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let this completely cool before adding the second layer.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: corn pudding
directions: In saucepan, melt butter or margarine. Heat up to bubbling and scramble eggs in butter. Turn off heat. Mix in cornbread mix until mixture is of a pastry consistency. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until pudding is firm and has a slight golden brown appearance. Serve hot.

title: whipped cream topping
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly. Set aside to cool. Cream together the rest of the ingredients. Blend to cooled flour mixture.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.

title: fruit and angel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cake and Cool Whip.
Top angel food cake slices with this mixture, then add Cool Whip on top of this.

title: yummy cheese ball
directions: In large skillet, fry the bacon; remove from skillet and drain on paper towels.
Chop or break cooled bacon into small pieces.
In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, bacon and green onions.
When mixed well, form 2 balls.
Cover and refrigerate 3-4 hours or overnight.
Before serving, roll the cheese balls in the chopped pecans.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, seasoned salt, chicken, vegetables, half the cheese and half can onions.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Separate crescent rolls into rectangles; press perforated cuts together.
Cut into strips.
Place on casserole to form lattice.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, for 3 to 5 minutes, until onions are golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mom's goulash
directions: Brown meat in frying pan with onion; drain and add salt and pepper, then add can of chopped tomatoes and simmer together for at least 10 minutes while macaroni noodles are boiling.
Once macaroni is finished, drain water out and add noodles and meat/tomato mixture together.
Simmer all contents for about 10 minutes, stirring, then serve.

title: creamed sweet potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, oleo milk and vanilla. Pour into a casserole dish.

title: new years day pork and sauerkraut(it brings good luck)
directions: Mix ingredients together in large roasting pan. Cover and bake at about 325° for 3 to 4 hours. Meat should fall off the bone. This is easily done early. I serve it with made ahead mashed potatoes.

title: peppered steak
directions: Mix soy sauce and water.
Pour on meat.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight, turning meat occasionally.
Remove meat and reserve marinade.

title: basic no-fat chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare pan(s) as directed in recipes. Heat evaporated milk in a medium size saucepan until barely simmering.
Remove from heat and whisk in cocoa until thickened and almost smooth (some tiny lumps will remain).
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes to cool slightly.
Whisk in applesauce and vanilla extract. Mix flour, 1 1/4 cups sugar, the baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Beat egg whites in medium size bowl with electric mixer on high until thick and foamy.
Gradually beat in remaining 1/4 cup sugar until stiff peaks form when beaters are lifted.
Pour cocoa mixture over flour.
Stir just until blended. With a rubber spatula gently stir about 1/4 egg whites into flour mixture.
Fold in remaining egg whites until no white streaks remain.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake until pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter.
Add peeled, cubed potatoes and enough water to cover potatoes.
Cook until tender. Do not drain.
Add corn, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat, do not boil. Great with corn muffins.

title: cap'n crunch munch
directions: Combine cereals, marshmallows and nuts in a deep bowl (Tupperware cake top).
Set this on top of hot boiler of water. Melt almond bark and pour over mixture.

title: bread and butter sticks
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In mixing bowl, combine biscuit mix, sugar and milk.
Stir with fork until a soft dough forms.
Beat 20 strokes until stiff, not sticky.
Turn out onto board dusted with biscuit mix; knead gently 10 times.
Roll to 8 x 8-inch rectangle.
Use floured knife to cut in half lengthwise, then cut each half crosswise into 8 strips.
In baking pan in which oleo is melted, dip each strip; coat each side.
Arrange strips in two rows in pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serves 16.
Makes 16 sticks.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken (or you can cook in crockpot). When chicken is done, remove and let cool.
Put the broth to the side. While chicken is cooling cook your rice as directed on package (I use old timey long grain rice). Take the broth and pour into your stock pot.

Add your soups to the broth. Cook over medium heat until blended. Debone chicken and cut into small pieces. Add chicken to broth mixture. When rice is done, add to broth mixture. You can add water if needed. Simmer over medium heat 10 or 20 min.

title: potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough flour to make the dough stiff.
Put in the refrigerator for 3 or 4 hours.
Take out of refrigerator 2 hours before cooking.
Cook at 325° for 2 hours.

title: pizza pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Add tomato paste, tomato sauce and spaghetti seasoning. Simmer for a few minutes. Pour into baking dish. Spread sour cream over meat. Sprinkle on cheese. Unroll crescent rolls and place on top of cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine the peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme. Mix until well combined. Add cereal and mix until well coated. Chill for a few minutes. Melt the morsels and shortening together and stir until smooth. Roll the cereal into balls the size of a large marble. Dip into the melted chocolate. Place on a wax paper-lined pan. Refrigerate until set. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine eggs and seasonings.
Shape meat mixture into 8 rolls. Wrap cabbage leaves around securely.
Pour soup into skillet; add cabbage rolls. Cover and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer 35 minutes, spooning sauce occasionally.
(This can be baked in the oven.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Reserve 1 cup chicken broth.
Combine soups, chili spices and chicken broth; blend.
Cover bottom of a greased 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish with 2 cups of chips. Spread 1/2 chicken over this.
Then layer 1/2 the sauce and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Put ingredients into a 9-inch round cake pan.
Stir until mixed well.
Make 3 holes in this mixture.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Combine margarine, peanut butter, sugar and cereal.
Mix well. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip into chocolate which has been melted in top of a double boiler with paraffin.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Mix together flour, oleo and pecans and bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and small carton of Cool Whip and spread on crust.
Mix the pudding and milk. Spread on cream cheese mixture.
Top with another carton of Cool Whip and spread pecans on top , if desired.

title: spicy pickled beets
directions: To cook beets, wash and drain.
Leave 2 inches of the stem and the tap roots.
Cover with boiling water and cook till tender. Drain; cool to handeling temperature.
Peel and jullienne. Combine vinegar, water, sugar and spices in pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5-10 minutes.
Strain out spices and add to beets.
Add onions and bring back to boil.
Pack hot beets in hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch head space.
Remove air bubbles and adjust caps.
Process in boiling water bath for 30 minutes.
Yield:
4 pints.

title: pecan logs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll mixture in desired size roll.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.
Large rolls can be sliced into bite-size pieces.

title: rhubarb pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and egg yolks.
Add flour, cinnamon, rhubarb and hot water.
Beat well.
Add egg whites, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450° and grease a cookie sheet.
Sift 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Add the Crisco and cut it into flour until the particles are the size of small peas.
Add mashed potato and water; stir.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Pour into graham cracker crust.
Very good (if you like peanut butter).

title: 49'ers
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: miracle cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 1-inch balls and press down with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: frozen pineapple dessert
directions: Cream the cream cheese at room temperature.
Prepare Dream Whip and add to cheese; mix well.
Add marshmallows and pineapple (with juice).
Mix well and freeze.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shirley's dessert
directions: Put 1 layer of cake, 1 layer of fruit, 1 layer of pudding until used up. Top with Cool Whip, nuts, etc. Chill - over night is best.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together 1 day before serving.
Makes kids love their vegetables.

title: mama's egg custard
directions: Cook in an unbaked pie crust for 45 minutes.

title: ohio noodles
directions: Cook noodles; grease dish.
Heat milk and add cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add bread, butter, pimentos, onion, salt and pepper.
Add eggs.
Pour over noodles.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Insert knife; if clean, it is done.

title: lazy man's beef stroganoff
directions: Cook 3 cans of soup and beef in crock-pot all day.
Just before serving, add sour cream and mushrooms.
Serve on rice or noodles.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Separately mix next 4 ingredients and pour over first mixture.
Refrigerate overnight. Delicious.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, butter, corn syrup and rest of ingredients, except pecans.
Put pecans in unbaked pie crust, then add liquid ingredients.
Bake at 400°.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Drop by teaspoon on greased sheet.
Dip glass in sugar and flatten.
Bake at 400° for about 3 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Spray a 2-quart casserole with vegetable spray.
Saute one onion with ground meat and season to taste.
Put meat in bottom of dish.
Put a layer of corn over top.
Spread mashed potato on top and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake about 35 minutes.

title: fast and easy hamburger gravy
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic. Salt and pepper to taste. Add gravy and mushrooms.
Heat through. Serve over rice.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice with dissolved sugar.
Add orange juice (undiluted).
Add Kool-Aid.
Pour into large container.
Finish filling container with water.
Freeze.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat oil.
Fry tortillas until soft.
Put in cheese, onion and sauce; roll.
Place in square dish.
Add rest of sauce and top with cheese.
Put in oven at 400° just until cheese melts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Mix eggs, flour, butter and cheeses together.
Add broccoli (chopped).
Pour into 8 x 12-inch greased glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yield:
6 servings.

title: dad's soup
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Add everything, except the beans. Bring to a boil, then simmer on low for 1 hour.
Add pork and beans.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Serves 6+.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix flour, sugar and Crisco with pastry blender or tablespoon and fork until in fine pieces. Add buttermilk to yeast; stir well and add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
(Add more milk if needed until dough is easy to handle.) Put dough in greased bowl and let rise 2 hours.
Then knead dough on floured surface.
Roll dough on wax paper and cut out biscuits. Let rise 2 hours.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown (8 to 10 minutes).

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together in a pot. Add can milk and stir well. Add butter and cook on high heat until mixture comes to full boil stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to med and boil at full boil for 3 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in 1 inch boiling salted water until tender.
Drain well.
Brown onion and carrot in half oleo in skillet.
Stir in 1/2 Stove Top.
Add soup, sour cream and squash.
Pour in 2-quart casserole.
Brown other half of Stove Top in remaining oleo and arrange on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can use cheese on top also.

title: giambotta
directions: Cover bottom of Dutch oven with olive oil.
Chop garlic. Saute carrots, onion, celery and garlic.
Add tomatoes, water, beans and zucchini.
Simmer for 1 hour or until veggies are cooked.
Season with basil, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.

title: aunt bessie isaac's vinegar pie
directions: Beat eggs well with mixer.
Mix sugar and flour together, then slowly to eggs while beating.
Add vinegar and water. Cook over low heat until thickened.

title: cheese balls
directions: Get all ingredients at room temperature and mix together. Chill for 4 hours.
After chilled, form into ball and roll in extra mixture of pecans and parsley.

title: autumn cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries.
Drain pineapple and add sugar and then add whipping cream.
Last, fold in marshmallows and chill.

title: sour cream rhubarb pie
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add sour cream, sugar, flour and rhubarb.
Stir.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pastry pie shell. Sprinkle nutmeg lightly on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Beat the egg whites and sugar until peaks form.
Remove pie from oven; spread with meringue.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes more, until meringue is brown.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda and set aside.
Mix brown sugar, egg, sour milk, oil, vanilla and rhubarb.
Add dry ingredients. Sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup brown sugar plus 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mini crab cakes
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat; add onion, and saut for 3 minutes.
Stir in celery and paprika.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes; cool.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Add dressing to sliced and chopped vegetables.
Chill and serve.
Store in refrigerator.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers on top of casserole.
Dot crackers with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood cancun
directions: Whip margarine and flour over heat until thick.
Add chicken bouillon; let thicken.
Add sour cream.
Shred imitation sea legs and place on flour tortilla.
Add some shredded Cheddar cheese. Roll up and place in glass casserole dish.
Pour cream mixture over rolls.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika for color.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender, except pimento.
Run on high until smooth.
Add pimento.
Run until chopped.
Serve on crackers or chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with crushed cornflakes and 1/3 cup butter during the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cake mix (dry), butter and egg in large bowl on low speed.
Press into ungreased rectangle pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in a saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir at least 1/2 of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil for 2 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples, sugar, cheese, flour, butter and spice together. Pour into bottom crust of pie.
Cover with other crust.
Make slits in top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Rinse peppers and cut a thin slice from stem end of each. Remove white fiber and seeds; rinse.
Drop peppers into boiling salted water to cover. Simmer for 5 minutes. Remove peppers from water.
Invert and set aside to drain.

title: ann's red rice
directions: Fry sausage and bacon.
Dice onions, peppers and mushroom and saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in 3 cups of rice.
Fry until brown. Add 4 cups tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for approximately 1 hour.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Toss carrots with other ingredients except brown sugar.
Turn into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup with mayonnaise, onion and eggs; mix well. Add broccoli and mix well.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish to make 2 inches thick.
Bake at 325° until set and firm.
Cheese can be added to the top the last few minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine broccoli, chicken broth, onion and nutmeg.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into blender, adding onion soup and butter.
Blend on high speed until smooth. Add sour cream and blend a few more seconds.
Serve hot or cold.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on chicken and brown in oil.
Put in baking dish.
Blend soup in drippings in pan.
Gradually stir in wine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Boil for 1 minute.
Pour over chicken.
Bake covered for 25 minutes, and uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet fig pickles
directions: Soak figs in boiling soda water and let stand 10 minutes. Drain and rinse twice in cold water.
Add vinegar, sugar and spice and bring to a hard boil for 30 minutes.
Pack into jars while boiling and seal.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order.
Then spread over with Miracle Whip.
Top with cheese.
Cover with Saran Wrap and let set overnight.
Put bacon bits on the next morning.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
(Microwave works good for this.) Mix pork and beans and brown sugar together and pour into a baking dish.
Top with pieces of broken bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered.
Uncover, stir and bake until desired consistency.

title: kugela
directions: Dice bacon and fry (reserve grease).
Hand grate potatoes and onion.
Mix everything including grease from bacon in large bowl. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until fork comes out clean.

title: chili
directions: Combine all in Dutch oven.
Cover and simmer on low approximately 1 hour.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in a large vessel as mixture foams while cooking.
Cook to soft ball stage on medium heat.
Remove from fire.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until creamy or until mixture changes color.
Drop quickly on previously salted wax paper.

title: baked macaroni dish
directions: Cook macaroni as on package.
Brown and drain ground beef. Drain macaroni and mix with ground beef and spaghetti sauce.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in a greased baking dish.
Layer with Mozzarella cheese and then add remaining mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top, then bake until cheese melts.

title: valentine cookies
directions: Beat butter until creamy. Beat in sugar gradually. Blend in egg, water and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and soda. Add to creamed mixture, blending well. Stir in oats.
For easier handling, chill dough about 1 hour. Roll out on floured board to 1/8-inch thick. Cut with heart shaped cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 350° oven about 12 minutes or until golden brown. When cool, frost with powdered sugar frosting tinted pink and leave some white.
May mix a little butter in with the frosting mix.

title: scottish steak pie(scotland)
directions: Brown and cook steak, onion and carrots half through.
Place meat, onion, carrots and potatoes in layers in buttered casserole. Add a little water to keep from sticking.
Season.
Cover with flaky pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Canned tomatoes may be substituted for water.
Yields 6 servings.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Beat well.
Add 1 cup pecans.
Pour into a large cookie sheet that has been well-greased.
Bake 20 minutes in 325° to 350° oven.

title: virgie's nutty delight pralines
directions: In thick walled pot over medium heat, melt sugar, evaporated milk, dash of salt and butter.
Add coconut, pecans and almonds. Cook over medium to low heat for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add almond extract.
Cool slightly.
Scoop onto waxed paper laid over paper towels with a small bladed ice cream scoop. Makes 38 to 42 pralines depending on size of scoop.
For firmer pralines, use 1/2 stick of butter.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 1 hour (until thickened).
Serve over rice.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add flour and flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all and chill.

title: three bell pepper relish
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except sugar and vinegar.
Toss.
Combine sugar and vinegar in medium, nonreactive saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over bell pepper mixture.
Stir to combine.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on box.
Punch holes in cake with a wooden spoon handle.
Mix milk and cream of coconut and pour over cake (hot) and through holes.
Top with mixture of coconut and Cool Whip after cake has cooled.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to a boil.
Add dry jello to boiling mixture.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Pour over fresh peaches.
Stir gently.
Place in baked pie shell.
Chill well. Serve with whipped cream.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Put oven at 350°.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until you can insert knife in middle and it comes out clean.

title: hot spiced tea(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine together; store in a tightly covered jar.
For 1 serving, place 1 rounded teaspoonful in a cup.
Add boiling water; stir and enjoy.

title: poor man soup(feeds 10)
directions: Brown meat; pour off grease.
Mix canned ingredients.
Season to taste with garlic and salt and pepper.

title: more casserole(called "more" because everyone always wants more!)
directions: Brown and season meat while macaroni is cooking.
After both are ready in large Dutch oven or large casserole, add all ingredients, cutting up Velveeta to make melting easier.
Cover and back at 350 degrees for approximately 20 to 30 minutes until cheese is melted and casserole is hot.
Delicious warmed up next day.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter or margarine.
Stir in mixed flour, salt and paprika.
Mix well (with hands is best way).
Mix 1 teaspoon of the dough around each olive.
Arrange on a flat pan and freeze.
Place in a plastic bag.
Store in your freezer.
When ready to use, remove from bag and arrange on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields 48 puffs.

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until fluffy.
Add walnuts; place in greased pan (9 x 13-inch) and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sirloin tip beef roast
directions: Remove roast from package. Trim excess fat from roast and rinse. Place in roaster pan and sprinkle all over with garlic salt. Place in preheated 500 degree oven for about 15 minutes, until tip is seared to seal in juices. Lower temperature to 350 degrees and bake until desired doneness (do not cover). 3 hours will give well done with medium done on inside. Take out of oven and place on platter. Place baking pan on burner and add 3 C water and stir. Bring to a boil. Add 4 Tbsp corn starch to 1/2 C water. Mix until smooth. Add to pan and stir until thickened. Slice roast and serve with gravy over roast or cooked rice.

title: hand lotion
directions: Beat in a large bowl of mixer until bowl is full.

title: holiday cider
directions: Slice orange into 6 wedges; stud with cloves and set aside. Combine cider with red hots in a large pot over medium heat.
Cook until red hots are dissolved and mixture is heated.
Pour into serving container.
Add orange wedges and cinnamon sticks.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Bake pie crust at 325° for 20 minutes.
Saut vegetables in butter until crisp but not soft.
Drain well.
Add seasonings. Place tomato, sliced, in bottom of pie crust.
Add vegetables. Spread mayo-cheese mixture over vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In large saucepan, melt together all ingredients until smooth. Add meatballs to sauce and simmer approximately 30 minutes. Place on table in fondue pot to keep warm. Spear meatballs with toothpick to serve.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the dates and soda.
Let stand while the remaining ingredients are being mixed.
Add mixture to the first mixture.
Bake in a moderate oven (360°) for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: rice pudding(dietetic)
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Set aside.
Mix pudding, milk and egg in saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rice.
Pour into dessert dishes and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: no-bake chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in saucepan. Bring to boil quickly. Reduce heat to medium and cook additional 3 to 4 minutes. Remove from heat and add oats and vanilla. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper and let stand until hardened.

title: honey and mustard pork tenderloin
directions: *Butterfly pork chops will also work.

title: strawberry-orange marmalade
directions: Cut 2 oranges into quarters; remove seeds.
Slice thinly (about 2 cups).
Cut 1 lemon in half lengthwise; slice thinly, removing seeds.
Remove rind from remaining orange and lemon with vegetable parer.
Cut into thin strips 1/16-inch wide and 2-inches long. Combine slices and rind in large kettle with water.
Bring to boiling; boil 30 minutes until soft.
Combine sugar and strawberries in large bowl; mash slightly.
Stir into kettle.
Boil 30 more minutes until liquid sheets from spoon.
Skim off foam; ladle into 5 hot 8 ounce jars.
Seal.
Process 10 minutes in simmering water bath (185°).
Cool; label and store in cool, dry place.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Saute hamburger meat, onion and green pepper.
Season with seasoned salt and 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with 1 pound Tater Tots.
Add meat mixture.
Add chicken soup, celery soup and mushroom soup.
Mix together and pour over meat mixture and Tater Tots.
Put 1 pound Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Cover with grated cheese and put back in oven and melt.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.

title: pudding cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on box.
Add dry cake mix and stir. Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ultra low-fat oven crispy onion-mushroom chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine mayonnaise and dry soup mix; let stand for 5 to 10 minutes so onion flakes will soften.

title: cheese ball
directions: After cream cheese is soft, mix all ingredients together. Roll into a ball and coat with additional nuts, if desired. Serve with crackers.

title: apple pudding
directions: Mix and let set apples and 1 cup white sugar, while you mix 1 cup white sugar and oleo.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add the above 4 cups sugar-coated apples.
Then add to apples the flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg or cloves, salt and nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or test with a toothpick.

title: shipwreck hash
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and celery. Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in bottom of casserole.
Mix kidney beans, tomatoes, tomato soup, sugar and 1/2 can water.
Pour over meat mixture. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: corvette date bars
directions: Crumble Oreos in blender (looks like potting soil).
In one bowl, mix milk, cream cheese and margarine. In second bowl, mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Combine both bowls together.

title: baked steak
directions: Place steak on large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place onion slices and mushrooms on top of steak. Pour Dale's steak sauce and water on top of onions and mushrooms. Close foil and secure edges.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.

title: whoopie cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Drop them by spoon on greased pan. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: ultimate macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package. Drain well. Return to same pan. Add Velveeta, milk and pepper to macaroni. Stir on low heat until Velveeta melts. Serve immediately. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Mix everything but cukes and bring to a boil for about 1 minute.
Put cukes in clean tight jars and cover with syrup.
(I double this recipe.)
Chill overnight before using.
Store in cool place and will keep all winter.
Syrup can be reused; just bring to a boil and add new cukes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain well.
Add taco seasoning and 1/4 cup water.
In casserole dish put Doritos and ground beef mixture in layers.
Top with cheese.
Put into oven for 20 minutes at 350° until cheese melts.
May top with chopped lettuce, chopped tomatoes and Old El Paso taco sauce.

title: zucchini with mint
directions: Thinly slice or grate slender zucchini,
If you grate, squeeze out water.
Quickly saute zucchini in hot olive oil with some minced garlic.
Stir in chopped parsley and mint to taste. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve warm or room temperature.

title: good cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place chocolate candy kiss on top.
Remove cookie with spatula to cooling rack.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Mix all remaining ingredients, then add oatmeal.
Bake at 350° until done about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: Cook chicken and chop into small pieces.
Chop pepper, pimentos, onions and celery.
Cook in chicken broth for 8 minutes. Add soup and mushrooms.
Cook in broth.
Add egg noodles; cook in broth.
Pour in a casserole dish.
Grate cheese and pour over top. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Dissolve dry milk in water in top of double boiler. Add sugar and stir until thick over boiling water, 17 minutes. Cool and use instantly or refrigerate. Makes 14 ounces.

title: mom's pound cake
directions: Mix butter and Crisco.
Then add sugar.
Beat until creamy. Then add 1 cup flour and 3 eggs.
Mix well.
Then add remaining flour and 3 eggs.
Next, add flavorings and pour into a greased, floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 300°.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and mayonnaise until smooth. Mix ham, parsley flakes, dry onion, dry mustard and Tabasco with cheese mixture; chill overnight. Roll into ball and roll over chopped pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: kids can do - play dough
directions: With adult supervision, mix ingredients in a saucepan and heat on low heat for 3 minutes.
Knead on wax paper.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 pound of play dough.

title: raspberry kuchen
directions: Place raspberries on top of the mixture in pan.
Mix eggs, milk, 2 tablespoons flour and 1 1/2 cups sugar together and pour over fruit.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, margarine and 1/2 cup flour. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a loaf.
Place in crock-pot with potatoes around top.
Cook at low all day.

title: collard greens
directions: Boil ham hocks for about 15 minutes.
Then add collards.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours on high.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco in an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Cream sugar with Crisco. Add eggs, 1 at a time. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa. Incorporate flour mixture with sugar and egg mixture, alternating flour mixture and milk. Add vanilla. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: corn and yellow rice casserole
directions: Stir it
all up.
Bake at 350°.
When it bubbles, cover with Cheddar cheese and melt.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Beat margarine or butter and sugar in bowl.
Beat in syrup, eggs and flour thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes; cool.
Cut into squares.

title: pam's florida shells
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix spinach, 1 cup Mozzarella, cottage cheese, egg white and Parmesan cheese until blended.
Fill each shell with a heaping tablespoonful of spinach mixture.
Place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish; spoon sauce over shells.
Cover with foil.
Sprinkle extra 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake 35 minutes in oven.
Makes 4 servings.

title: party-on party dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in bottom of baking dish, pour can of chili over and top with shredded cheeses.
Bake at 325 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: homemade ointment
directions: Melt all ingredients on low heat in iron skillet until smooth in texture.
Seal tight and store in small jars.
Use as needed for cuts and sores.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Bring to a boil.
Cover apples and bake until golden brown and apples are tender.

title: microwave tater tot casserole
directions: Season ground beef with salt, pepper and minced onion.
Place in glass casserole and top with a paper towel.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes; drain fat.
Pour 1 can of soup over meat.
Place Tater Tots on top and add the second can of soup.
Sprinkle cheese and paprika on top.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes; rotate twice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dabo kolo(bread snack)
directions: Mix all ingredients and knead until smooth.
Roll into long, thin strips (thin pencil size) and snip off into 1/4-inch pieces. (You can make a variety of colors of leave natural.)
Spread pieces on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for about 20 minutes or until firm.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil.
Dissolve jello in apricot nectar; add to cake batter and mix well.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325° in greased and floured tube pan.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300° to 325°.

title: cold slaw
directions: Stir mixture until sugar dissolves.
Use this mixture in chopped cabbage.
Use enough to moisten cabbage.
Some cabbage should be left over to be used at a later date.

title: twice potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into cooking dish.
Bake until cheese has melted and is hot.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot.

title: camp stew
directions: Layer bacon on the bottom of pot with tight fitting lid.
Layer stew meat on top of bacon.
Dump both cans of potatoes and juice from cans in pot.
Dump both cans and juice of carrots in pot. Dump can of onions and juice in (not necessary).
Cover pot and put pot in or on campfire; leave for about 45 minutes.
Don't open until done.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Unroll the roll and spread filling.
Roll back up.
Chill and serve.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Fix jello and add sherbet.
Mix.
Cool in refrigerator until thick as egg whites.
Add oranges and juice.
Whip cream and fold in.
Pour into mold.
Chill.

title: reba's microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine the brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt in a quart dish.
Microwave mixture on High 4 to 5 minutes, until it boils. Add the baking soda; stir until foamy.
Spray Pam inside a large brown paper bag; place popcorn inside.
Pour sauce over corn; microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes and shake.
Microwave 1 minute; shake.
Microwave 45 seconds; shake.
Microwave 30 seconds; shake. Pour onto cookie sheet to cool.

title: roquefort sour cream dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed.
Drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Stir Parmesan cheese into casserole and also sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hazel's soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream well sugar, shortening and eggs; dissolve soda in milk and add.
Add cream of tartar to flour.
Add vanilla to mixture and mix in.
Add flour to mixture and mix smooth.
Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Place on cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cabbage
directions: Wash and core cabbage; place cabbage on 2 pieces of overlapping Saran Wrap.
Spread butter in cavity of cabbage; pour soy sauce in cavity.
Wrap cabbage tightly and place in a glass pie plate.
Microwave at High for 10 to 12 minutes or until fork-tender, rotating cabbage every 5 minutes.
Let stand, wrapped, 5 minutes.

title: jonathan bunce's blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line muffin tin with paper liners (10 to 12 muffins)).
Mix egg, milk and oil together.
Add all dry ingredients.
Mix well, but do not overmix.
Fold in blueberries. Fill each muffin cup about 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Beat into egg mixture with vanilla.
Fold in apples, walnuts and coconut.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Fill gallon jar with clean cucumbers (any size).
Add alum, salt and pickling spice.
Cover cucumbers with vinegar.
Set for 3 months or longer.
Cover.
When you are ready to use, drain liquid.
Cut cucumbers into slices.
Add 2 cups sugar per quart of cucumbers.
Pack in jars.
Refrigerate.

title: cheesy spaghetti bake
directions: Brown meat and onions. Drain. Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 10 minutes. Add cooked spaghetti. Melt butter; stir in flour and salt. Slowly add milk and water. Stir over medium heat until thickened. Add Parmesan cheese and half of American cheese. Stir until melted. Spread half of spaghetti mixture in long baking dish. Spoon all cheese mixture over. Add remaining spaghetti mixture. Top with American cheese. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked sliced ham with pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place ham in baking pan.
Pour pineapple juice over ham; cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Mix brown sugar and mustard and spread over ham.
Place halved pineapple on ham.
Return to oven and bake uncovered 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Baste frequently with juices from bottom of pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Place in one pie crust.
Cover with other pie crust.
Cut slits in top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in
a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Mix other ingredients together and
put
in
the
pan.
Cook at 400° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: graham crackers delight
directions: Cook butter, sugar and nuts and boil about 3 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers and cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch carefully because it burns quickly.

title: homemade apple pie
directions: Mix shortening, flour and water until thick.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch larger than pie pan.
Place into pan.
Pour apples into pan over crust and spread evenly.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Combine cranberries, water and sugar in a saucepan.
Let boil until berries pop, 5 minutes.
Peel apples, then slice.
Stir into berry mixture.
Pour into baking dish.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese and taco seasoning in bottom of dish.
Add remaining ingredients as listed in recipe.
Serve with tortilla chips and enjoy!

title: baked bean chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook beef over medium heat and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Place in a 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Mix beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into meatballs.
Brown in skillet.
Drain.
Add soups, water, onion, soy sauce, rice and peas.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with crackers, followed by grated cheese. Bake until cheese melts.

title: deliciously simple chicken
directions: You will need 1 large (14 x 20-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: cherry stuff
directions: In a large bowl, dump all ingredients; stir well.
Put a few nuts on top.

title: bouquet garni no. 2
directions: Put herbs in the middle of a coffee filter.
Gather up into a bag and tie with string.
Store garni in an airtight glass jar. Use to flavor soups or stews.

title: italian casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until tender.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, salt, basil, oregano, sugar and pepper.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Bring all the ingredients to a boil.
Simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.
Just before serving, mix a little flour and milk together and add to soup to thicken it.
Very good!

title: pizza delight
directions: Preheat oven.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt, oil and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth (about 5 minutes).
Place in a greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place 45 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough out flat and then fit into 9-inch pie pan.
Cut off excess dough and put aside.
Spread sauce, enough to taste; add desired toppings.
The excess dough that was cut, roll flat and cut into strips about 1-inch wide and lay over top.
Place in oven and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut and serve.
You can eat warm or cold.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook all ingredients together until almost no juice is left. Put in casserole dish.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: angel custard
directions: Make a custard of the above.
Cook custard until thick. Dissolve an envelope of plain gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water and put into custard mixture while still hot.
Let cool.
Fold in:
1 pt whipped cream, 4 egg whites beaten stiff and 1/4 tsp almond extract.
Break angel food cake into chunks.
Line large flat pan with chunks.
Pour custard over all.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
A few hours before serving, ice with 1/2 pint whipped cream and sprinkle with toasted sliced almonds. Makes 12 servings.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add crushed graham cracker crumbs. Add eggs, one at a time, along with other ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into cake pans (usually takes at least 3 pans).
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars together.
Add eggs, water and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
In another bowl, mix the flour, salt and baking soda together with a fork.
Add dry ingredients slowly to the butter-sugar mixture and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: drop chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Stir together in saucepan. Bring to a hard boil and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by tablespoons on waxed paper and let cool.

title: shrimp on the grill
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over the shrimp in a glass dish. Marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes. Drain and reserve sauce to baste.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Rinse in cold water; drain.
Combine rest of ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour on dressing and toss.
Marinate overnight or several days, as this keeps well.

title: vonnie's pretzels
directions: Mix in a large pan; sprinkle the salad dressing over mixture. Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, dill and salt; mix well.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and butter, mixing only until flour is moistened.
Stir in nuts, spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Can be frozen when completely cooled.

title: tom and jeff's "harmony" chicken
directions: Prepare stuffing as box directs.
Cool.
Pound chicken breasts with mallet until slightly flattened.
Place slice of Swiss cheese and spoonful of dressing on each piece of chicken and roll up, securing with a toothpick.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until tender.
About halfway through baking, pour cream of mushroom soup, that is thinned with milk to desired consistency, over chicken and finish baking.

title: little fruit cookies
directions: Work butter until soft and creamy.
Add sugar gradually until smooth.
Beat in eggs thoroughly.
Stir in flour combination and all chopped fruit and nuts.
Batter will be very thick.
Spoon or shape dough, about 1 teaspoon, into round, flat sizes.
Dough will rise a little.
Bake at 400° approximately 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Reserve 1/4 cup and set aside.
Place remainder of crumbs in bottom of pie shell.
Mix pudding according to directions; let set 3 to 5 minutes until thick.
Then pour over crumbs in pie shell.
Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes.
Cover with Cool Whip and top with reserved crumbs. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Mix the jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Mix the cinnamon drops with 1/2 cup boiling water.
Stir until drops are dissolved. Add to jello mixture.
Add applesauce; mix well.
Chill.

title: cherry crumble dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, layer pineapple, cherry pie filling and then dry cake mix. Pour melted margarine over cake mix, then sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well in mixer and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat pear juice to boiling; add jello (dissolve).
Chill until partly set.
Dice pears.
Whip Dream Whip until stiff; add soft cream cheese and mix well with electric mixer.
Add partly set jello; mix lightly.
Fold in diced pears and nuts.
Put into a 8 x 8-inch glass pan.
I use a pretty crystal dish.
Sprinkle nuts on top, refrigerate and spoon out to serve.

title: taco bake
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Add beans, tomato sauce and seasoning. Lay 2 shells in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add mix; lay 2 more shells on top of mix.
Add 1 can water to soup; stir and pour over shells.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with Cheddar cheese after 50 minutes.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix and chill dough.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake until set.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Drain pineapple and set aside.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and juice from pineapple.
Cook mixture over medium heat until thickened (5 to 10 minutes).

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and pour over sugar and peanut butter.
Mix together.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Roll into balls.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in iron skillet.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top, then place pineapple on top of that.
Beat eggs until light. Add gradually salt and sugar.
Heat milk to boiling.
Add to 1 tablespoon butter.
Beat into egg mixture; add vanilla.
Add flour to egg mixture.
Beat quickly until blended.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: In 2-quart pan cook onions in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is hot.
Makes 4 (3/4 cup) servings.
May substitute spinach, cauliflower or asparagus for broccoli.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Core the mushrooms. Chop about 2/3 of the stems and mix with the rest of the ingredients well. Stuff each mushroom cap. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Broil for 4-5 minutes before serving.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, grated onion, lemon juice and salt and spread on a shallow platter.
Pour cocktail sauce over and spread evenly on top.
Then add crab meat (real or imitation).
Sprinkle dried parsley on top of crab meat.

title: smoke flavored roasted chicken
directions: Mix soy, sherry, smoke flavoring, ginger juice, hoisin sauce and salt.
Place chicken and mixture in plastic tie bag.
Shake to spread sauce evenly over chicken. Keep chicken in bag at least 4 hours.

title: eggplant pizza round
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 35 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion. Drain. Add can of tomatoes, macaroni, soup, water and butter. Cook over low heat until macaroni is tender. Add cheese. Stir and serve.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix all ingredients except spaghetti which is added last. Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil; top with 1/2 cup cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: pistachio chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and coconut over bottom of pan.
Mix all other ingredients, except chocolate syrup.
Reserve 1 cup batter and mix with the chocolate syrup.
Pour cake mix over the chocolate chips and coconut.
Then pour chocolate cake mix over the other batter. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana sour cream walnut loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and bananas and beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately with sour cream to banana mixture, stirring just to blend.
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon batter into two 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pans (or 24 muffin cups) that have been greased and floured on the bottom only.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes, or until cake tester comes out clean.
Let stand in pan on rack for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cool thoroughly.
Wrap in foil or plastic.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Grease baking sheets; set aside.
Soften yeast in warm water; set aside.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add shortening, yeast and buttermilk.
Stir just until dough clings together.
Knead gently on lightly floured surface 10 to 12 strokes.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheets, folding biscuit circles in half.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ohio noodles
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and place in well-greased baking dish. Heat milk.
Add cheese that has been cut in small pieces.
Stir until melted.
Add crumbs, butter, pimentos, onion, salt and pepper.
Add beaten eggs.
Pour over noodles; bake until knife inserted comes out clean.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven.
Very good.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef.
Season and add onion.
Continue cooking until onion is tender.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to meat. Simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: Combine all in an electric blender; blend until smooth and pale green.

title: uncooked raspberry jam
directions: Stir berries and sugar.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Boil pectin, MCP or Sure-Jell and 1 cup water for 1 minute.
Pour into fruit and stir 2 minutes.
Then pour into containers and store in freezer.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix and form crust on 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: fruit cup dessert
directions: Combine ingredients, tossing lightly until well mixed.
Cover and chill in refrigerator.
May be served as a salad.

title: butterscotch blondies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until golden brown and center is set.

title: popcorn christmas trees
directions: Measure popped corn into a large bowl.
Melt oleo and Marshmallow Creme in a large saucepan over low heat.
Drizzle over corn, stirring to mix and coat.
When cool enough to handle, grease hands and shape into Christmas trees, using 1 cup packed mixture for each.
Press in cinnamon candies to resemble lights. Top with a jellied candy.
Makes 12 trees.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly spray 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch square casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into dish.
Place dish on shelf in lower 1/3 of oven.
Bake for approximately 25 minutes until set in the middle and lightly golden brown on top.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In saucepan, add sugar, butter and milk. Cook on medium heat. Bring to boil 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat. Add oats and peanut butter, then vanilla. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper; cool.

title: zucchini, tomatoes and cheese
directions: Peel and slice zucchini very thin. Layer 1/3 of the zucchini in a slightly greased casserole dish. Cover with 1 can of the stewed tomatoes, including juice, and 1/3 of the shredded colby cheese. Repeat 2 more times, for a total of 3 layers. Top with crisp bacon slices. Bake for 1-1/2 hours in 350° oven. Makes 8 servings.

title: baked cheese
directions: Beat cream cheese; add sour cream, onion, bacon and cheese. Spoon in enough mayo for good consistency (not more than 3/4 cup). Pour into 9-inch square dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve warm with assorted crackers.

title: broiled spicy zucchini
directions: In a small bowl, combine the oil, onion, basil, red pepper flakes and salt.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Cut each zucchini lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Lay slices on baking sheet.
Brush the zucchini slices with half of the oil mixture. Preheat broiler.
Broil 2 inches from heat source 5 to 7 minutes or until browned.
Repeat with remaining oil mixture.

title: easy time squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and vanilla, stirring well. Spread batter on greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Top with pie filling and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and chill for several hours. Shape into ball and roll in additional chopped nuts.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain beans slightly, saving some juice.
Mix ketchup, brown sugar and molasses together with juice.
Stir into beans.
Pour into baking dish.
Cut up bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Lay on top of beans.

title: crab 'n rice
directions: First wash crab; remove biters and put aside.
Separate crab bodies from backs; scoop out crab fat into bowl.
Break bodies into sections; beat bodies and biters with coach beater.
Set aside. Peel and chop onion and sweet pepper; fry until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, crab fat and seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add 3 cups of water.
Bring to boil and add peas and crab.
Bring to boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add rice and bring back to boil.
Turn to simmer and cover pot until water is almost gone.
Cook on low until rice is tender.

title: bucket in the sky chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and set aside.
Put butter in bottom of baking dish.
Put chicken and dry mixture in bag and shake.
Put in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Hollow out a loaf (round) of pumpernickel bread; use as bowl for dip. Cube bread from loaf to dip.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter together until thick (about 5 or 10 minutes).
Add peanut butter, vanilla and marshmallows; stir. Let cool for a few minutes.
Beat with spoon until thick.
Pour on buttered plate.

title: fruit punch for 20
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Serve chilled.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients and place in ice cream freezer.

title: one hour breakfast
directions: Trim crust off all bread.
Butter 6 slices and place buttered side down in 9 x 13-inch pan (glass preferred).
Spread ham over bread.
Top the ham with slices of cheese.
Butter the other 6 slices of bread, place them on the cheese, buttered side up.
In mixing bowl beat eggs and add milk and dash of pepper.
Pour over ingredients in pan, melt 1/2 c. butter and drizzle over top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken carib
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, water, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper (after mixing together in bowl) to chicken in pan.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes; stir occasionally. Add rice to pan.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: candy bird nest
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter; pour over crumbled Shredded Wheat; put on wax paper.
Shape into bird nest.
Put tiny jelly beans in as they represent eggs.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: next best thing to robert redford dessert
directions: Mix and press to the bottom and partial sides of a baking dish.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook mushrooms and green pepper in butter for 5 minutes. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add cream and cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add turkey, pimiento and sherry.
Heat.
Divide spaghetti into 6 broiler-safe individual baking dishes or put into 1 shallow baking dish.
Add a small amount of turkey mixture to egg yolks; then stir in remaining mixture.
Pour over spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.
Put under broiler to brown lightly.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cheese danish
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Separate biscuits; place on baking sheet and flatten to 4 - inches in diameter.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over biscuits.
Distribute pineapple evenly over cream cheese.
Top with almonds.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until biscuits are browned.

title: papa jack's red beans and rice
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and
beat
at
least
5 minutes. Grease and flour 3 cake pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with 7 minute frosting.
While you are making your frosting, boil 1 cup water and 1 cup sugar for 8 minutes.
Stir
in	1
cup of fresh coconut.
Spoon on each layer before you put frosting on.
This makes the cake moist. Frost with
Seven
Minute
Frosting.
I
use
2 fresh, grated coconuts or	2
packages of fresh, frozen coconut, to which I add 1 cup of confectioners sugar.

title: potato bake
directions: Drain potatoes and place in baking dish.
Add enough dressing to make moist.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with cheese and sprinkle with bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon and cheese bits
directions: Cook and drain bacon, then cool and crumble bacon.
Add grated Swiss cheese, mushrooms and mayonnaise.
Mix together well. Spread on bread (cut into fourths if using whole slices).
Broil until brown, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hot fruit soup
directions: Heat sugar and water
in small saucepan. Add strawberries and cook slowly for 5 minutes. Add butter and lemon juice.
Add raspberries and blackberries. Transfer immediately to bowls and add a scoop of ice cream.
Serve at once. Serves 2.
Can double easily.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add chili block, cut into slices. Stir beans into mixture.
Add tomato juice and seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer.

title: deep dish apple pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, combine apples, white sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Gently toss to coat apples.
Spoon into baking dish.
In another bowl, combine brown sugar, melted butter and flour.
Mix until texture is crumbly.
Nuts may be added.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve with milk or cream.

title: rhode island blueberry slump(vintage recipe)
directions: Combine flour and baking powder.
Add butter and shortening. Cut in.
Add milk, all at once.
Stir until moist and form into a ball, handling as little as possible; set aside.
Place berries, sugar, water and lemon juice in a deep saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Drop dough one teaspoon at a time onto the fruit mixture around the edge of the pan.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes, until dumplings are cooked.
Place dumplings into individual dessert dishes and spoon blueberries over them.
Serve warm or cold with heavy cream.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: shrimp in cognac and cream(rich)
directions: Split cleaned shrimp down backs without cutting all the way through.
Melt butter in a large skillet. Add shrimp and saute over medium heat for about 5 minutes or until pink.
Season shrimp with salt, pepper and nutmeg to taste.
Heat cognac in a small pan.
Ignite and pour over shrimp.
Tilt the pan back and forth until the flames die down.
Simmer the shrimp over low heat for about 5 minutes and remove pan from heat.
Beat egg yolks and heavy cream and gradually stir mixture into pan juices. Reheat pan, if necessary. Do not let sauce boil!
Serve over wild rice. Serves 6.

title: brown velvet cake
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Beat shortening and sugar in a bowl.
Beat in eggs until mixture is light and fluffy.
Stir in chocolate.
Combine milk and vanilla. Add alternately with dry ingredients, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.

title: easy bake cod
directions: Place fish in a lightly greased baking dish.
Pour margarine over the fish.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: spicy cinnamon apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Mix with apples.
Put into pastry-lined shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Fold edge of top crust under and press together.
Flute edge; brush crust with milk.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
Bake at 425° until apples are tender when pricked with a fork.

title: grandma luciano's clam sauce
directions: Drain clams, saving liquid.
Saute onions and garlic in oil. Add remaining ingredients to pot, except clam juice; simmer 15 minutes.
Add clam juice.
Simmer additional 4 minutes, then remove bay leaf.
Serve over favorite pasta with salad and bread.

title: recipe to preserve children
directions: Mix children and dogs.
Empty them into field, stirring continually. Sprinkle with flowers.
Pour brook gently over pebbles.
Cover with a deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
When children are well browned, place in bath tub.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place nuts in bottom of a greased Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits into quarters; coat with mixture of granulated sugar and cinnamon. Drop coated biscuit pieces into Bundt pan.
Mix together the brown sugar and margarine; pour over the top of the biscuits. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: johnny's chicken casserole(serves 8)
directions: Cook chicken in salted water.
Cool and cut up.
In a casserole dish (large 2-quart), place 1/2 of the chicken.
Spread 1 can of soup over, add 1/2 of the dressing.
Repeat.
Beat eggs with a fork.
Pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: virginia corn relish
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes or until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Let cool.
Refrigerate relish in airtight container for 2 days to allow flavor to blend.

title: cottage cheese jello dessert
directions: Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese; stir in pineapple and Dream Whip.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves or 1 large Bundt pan.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Arrange asparagus in an oblong Pyrex dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over asparagus.
Lift asparagus lightly so mixture can penetrate to bottom.
Refrigerate.
May be marinated up to 36 hours ahead.
Serve chilled.

title: pink fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill in refrigerator.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Combine garlic, oil and dry dressing mix.
Pour over meat and allow to marinate in refrigerator at least 4 hours, preferably overnight.
Cook on outdoor grill at 400° for about 40 minutes, turning once.

title: uncle dewey's biscuits
directions: Cut lard
into	flour until it is mixed up to look like corn meal.
Add milk until you have a soft dough.
Roll out on floured surface
and
cut out.
Place in greased pan and also grease top of	biscuits.
Cook
in
oven
for
15 to 20 minutes or until light brown on top and bottom of biscuits.

title: easy barbecue casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Combine ingredients with hand mixer (except almonds).
Place in ovenproof dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove to chafing dish and serve with crackers.

title: one hundred good cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars; add oil and egg.
Beat well.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Add gradually to mixture. Stir in coconut, Rice Krispies, oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 100 cookies (approximately).

title: carousel salad bowl
directions: Cook creamettes according to directions on package.
Do not chill.
While still hot, drizzle with oil and vinegar.
Add onions, seasonings and cheese; toss well.
Gently mix in remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce.

title: strawberry cranberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
In a separate container, mash bananas.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Mix all this together and spread half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch dish. Then place in refrigerator until congealed.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and spread over 12-inch pizza pan to cover. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice until creamy.
Spread over cookie dough and arrange cut fruit on top.
Sprinkle a little powdered sugar on top or mix a little powdered sugar with some fruit juice left over from any canned fruit you used and pour over like a glaze.

title: holiday bits cutout cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl on low speed electric mixer until blended well. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to butter mixture, stirring until well blended. Divide dough in half. Cover; refrigerate 1 to 2 hours. Heat oven to 400°. On lightly floured surface, roll out each half of dough to 1/4-inch thick. Cut into desired shapes. Bake 6 to 8 minutes until light brown. Cool completely. Decorate as desired.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls onto cookie sheet. Bake according to directions. Mix the next 3 ingredients. Spread on top of cooled crust. Arrange veggies on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar and vanilla together.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour gradually and mix well.
The dough is soft and will be easiest to work with if cooled for an hour or so before using.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; beat until smooth.
Add Cool Whip; stir until fully mixed.
Use with fresh fruit.

title: cream candy
directions: Mix all ingredients; stir until dissolved. Place on heat and stir. Do not stir after mix starts to boil. Cook to 258°. Pour onto a buttered marble slab; roll and cut with scissors into pieces.

title: orangeade
directions: Combine water and sugar in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add juices.
Add water to make 2 quarts.
Chill before serving.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Drain and marinate
in the Italian salad dressing for 3 or 4 hours
or
more
the
artichoke
hearts, olives and green beans. Before
serving, add zucchini, tomatoes and mushrooms. Toss. Drain and serve.

title: mrs. levenia orlidge's coal crystal flowers(a lovely flower)
directions: "He will take your daughters to be perfumers and cooks and bakers."
1 Samuel 8:13

title: almond roca
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet.
Add sugar, stirring constantly, until dissolved.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add 2 1/2 packages of almonds.
Cool at least 7 minutes or longer, until mixture turns deep amber brown.
The almonds have to pop and the oil works in.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
When hard, melt chocolate and cover.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice.
Add gelatin; dissolve and allow to cool.
Add buttermilk to cooled gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped topping and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: macaroni pea salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain well.
Drain pimentos and peas.
Mix together and add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill before serving.

title: cheesecake
directions: Bring cream cheese, sour cream and butter to room temperature. Beat with mixer.
Add sugar, cornstarch and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix until smooth.
Take your 9-inch spring-form pan and line with aluminum foil, then pat with butter.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until top is golden brown.
Turn oven off and let set for 1 hour in the oven.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften dry yeast in warm water.
Combine all other ingredients in mixing bowl (except flour), adding the softened yeast after the unbeaten egg.
Then add the flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover.

title: fruity rice(this is a particularly sweet rice recipe.)
directions: Place peaches in a baking dish and set aside.
In saucepan, blend brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and spices in peach syrup. Stir in vinegar and butter; bring to a boil.
Cook until mixture is clear and thick, stirring frequently.
Pour over peaches.
Set in a 350° oven.
Immediately start on dough.

title: chicken salad(serves 8)
directions: Combine all. Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: quick mix chocolate cake
directions: Mix in ungreased long cake pan first 5 ingredients.
Stir well with spoon.
Then make 3 holes.
Put vanilla in one hole, oil in second hole and vinegar in the third hole.
Then pour over that the cold water and stir well.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until well done.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt ingredients in a saucepan.
Pour over popcorn; stir. Bake, uncovered, at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: fondue italiano
directions: In saucepan brown ground beef; drain off excess fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Add cheese gradually; stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Blend together cornstarch and wine; add to cheese mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
If fondue becomes too thick, add a little warmed Chianti.
Transfer to fondue pot; place over fondue burner.
Serve with Italian bread cut in bite-size pieces.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and lemon.
Add pumpkin and dry ingredients.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
You may add 1/2 cup raisins and 1/2 cup nuts at your pleasure.

title: middle east eggplant salad
directions: Cook eggplant ahead of time in oven or grill (turning it often so it cooks evenly) until very tender.
(It will look mushy.)
Let it cool down.
Peel and dice (skin should peel off easily).
Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.

title: lemon brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix water, sugar and yeast.
Let stand until bubbly, then mix in cake mix and 2 cups flour.
Beat well with mixer.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour.
Mix well.
Knead in remaining 1/2 cup flour (may need a little more flour).
Form in small balls, put in greased pan and let stand until double.
Makes good rolls or bread loaves.
