Bake rolls 25 minutes at 375°.
Bake loaves 35 minutes at 375°.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Mix all other
dry
ingredients.
Add
to sugar mixture alternately
with the milk.
Mix
well.
Fold
in
prunes
and nuts.
Bake in oblong pan that has been greased and floured at 300° until firm.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in uncovered casserole 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quick hot dog dish
directions: Brown hot dogs and onion.
Pour in tomato sauce, pepper, salt and chili.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Boil water and sugar until dissolved.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Put into paper cups and freeze.
Thaw slightly before serving.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Layer all ingredients in punch bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Wash and slice strawberries. Sprinkle with small amount of sweetener and set aside. Mix 1 1/2 cups sweetener, cornstarch and water. Cook until clear. Add Jell-O. Stir well and cool. Stir in strawberries and pour mixture into pie shell. Top with Cool Whip.

title: konnie's million dollar brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla and Choco-Bake.
Add coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Kim's Boiled Frosting.

title: italian bean bake
directions: Rinse and sort beans.
Solve salt in cold water in large container.
Add beans, soak overnight.
In large pot add drained beans, hot water and salt.
Cover, cook slowly until tender (add boiling water if needed).
Drain.
Melt butter and add onions. Cook slightly.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring until sauce thickens.
Break up tomatoes and blend into sauce.
Toss cheeses together.
Reserve 2 cups for top.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Turn into 4 (12 x 20 x 2-inch) pans. Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: squash pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
In large bowl with electric mixer, cream the butter, sugar and lemon peel until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition, at low speed.
Gradually add flour.
Mix alternately with sour cream until smooth; stir in squash.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan or wire rack for 10 minutes.
Turn out cake; cool completely. Drizzle icing over cake.

title: heavenly carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots until tender-crisp.
Place cooked carrots, pepper slices and onion slices in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and heat, stirring until well blended.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight.
Keeps well. Serves 16.

title: louise greeley dip
directions: Chop all fine and mix well.

title: cabbage plate
directions: Combine vegetables.
Add sugar, salt and oil.
Mix.
Add water and cook until just tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add 1 teaspoon of sugar and stir; set aside.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in buttermilk and yeast water.
(Batter is very moist.)
It is ready to store in refrigerator until needed or make into biscuits.

title: candied pecans
directions: Mix sugar and egg white.
Add pecans and mix well.
Place margarine on cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 325°.
Put cookie sheet in oven and completely melt margarine.
Place pecan mixture on cookie sheet and spread out.
Bake pecans for 45 minutes, removing every 10 minutes to turn nuts over.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix Niblets and cream-style corn.
Place in a shallow buttered casserole.
Top with cheese and cracker pieces.
Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over cracker mixture.
Pour over melted butter or dot with butter.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: jewish lightning
directions: Wash chicken in cold water. Cut into pieces or leave whole, as desired. Place in kettle with 2 or more quarts of water, enough to cover chicken. Cover and boil for 1 1/2 hours. Skim off top foam. Add coarsely chopped vegetables and seasoning. Cover and simmer for 4 hours. Remove chicken and vegetables; strain for clear soup. Broth will be golden yellow and very concentrated. Excellent for ill persons who cannot tolerate solid foods. Chicken can, of coarse, be used for salads, etc. Discard vegetables.

title: beef and spaghetti in chili
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°. Baking Time: 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred or chop cabbage; core apples but do not peel.
Dice apples; add pineapple.
Mix salad dressing, vinegar and some sweetener (to taste).
Add this to other ingredients just before serving.
This tends to get watery if it stands too long.
Toss lightly and put in serving bowls. Yield:
4 cups.
Carbohydrate 8 g, protein 1 g, fat 3 g, calories 63.
One serving = 1 vegetable exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: buttercream candy
directions: Boil to soft ball stage (tested in cold water).
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Beat if you want plain, or add nuts, candied fruit, coconut, peanut butter, etc., before beating.
Beat and when it is right consistency, put on waxed paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Combine the flour and rolled oats.
Cut in the margarine until mixture is crumbly; mix in 1/3 c. of the sugar.
Set aside for topping.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Cut off onion tops; even up onions on bottom to sit flat. Sprinkle with seasonings and herbs.
Dot with butter.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.

title: sugar-free cream cheese mints
directions: Mix ingredients together; chill and serve.

title: alabama cornbread
directions: Grease pan.
Mix ingredients well.
Pour in pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook in crock-pot on low for 6 hours.

title: pastel bavarian dessert
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Prepare 2 layer pans with Pam spray.
I use 8-inch or 9-inch or heart shape pans.
Bake as directed.
Cool cakes on rack.
Split each into 2 layers for filling.

title: light crab cheese ball
directions: Cut crabmeat into small pieces.
Mix with 1/4 to 1/2 cup of Cheddar cheese and rest of ingredients.
Shape into a ball and roll in rest of Cheddar cheese.
Chill 1 hour and serve with a variety of crackers.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with water.
Add ketchup and spices.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch (directions on box for thickening).
Serve on hot dogs with chopped onions and mustard.

title: taco salad for a crowd
directions: Combine meat, cheese, dressing and seasonings in large bowl. Add vegetables; combine well.
Toss with crushed Doritos just before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in Dutch oven and boil 1/2 hour.
Add cheese and soup.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pack into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 3 1/2 pints.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water; let cool.
Mix lemonade and pineapple juice with mixture.
Let stand a few minutes; stir well and freeze.
Let set for 2 hours before serving, then add 1 to 2 liters of 7-Up or Sprite.
Should be slushy.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Cook ground beef; set aside.
Cook macaroni.
In a large pan, combine soup and vegetables; cook to warm.
Combine vegetables, ground beef and cooked macaroni; put in a large casserole dish. (You may sprinkle top with shredded cheese of your choice.)
Place in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Take out and serve a tasty and easy meal.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and apples together.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Delicious.

title: orange-glazed cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice, salt and baking powder.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Heat soup and cheese until cheese is melted.
Add stuffing mix.
Combine with broccoli.
Put in baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: company beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, drain; add onion, tomatoes, ketchup, steak sauce, pepper and parsley.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni according
to
package directions.
Combine macaroni and
ground beef
mixture in a baking dish.
Season to taste. Gently
spoon soup
into
mixture.
Mix lightly, lifting from bottom.
Sprinkle cheese
over
top, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry dream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crush pretzels.
Mix pretzels, sugar and butter (melted).
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar in large bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Spread on top of cooled crust.
Mix Jell-O with boiling water; mix well.
Add cold water and partly thawed strawberries.
Put on top.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on crackers or put in tart shells.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on box; don't overcook. Drain well.
Saute garlic which has been minced in margarine for a few minutes.
Add soup and the 1 can of milk and sour cream; mix well. Heat thoroughly.
Add the well drained cooked pasta.
Salt and pepper.
Stir well; pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese easter eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and knead into a smooth dough. Form into candy size balls and let set on wax paper covered cookie sheet in cool place overnight.
Coat with chocolate.
Be sure to use margarine not butter.

title: easy cheesy brunch casserole
directions: Place bread slices in bottom of a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish; set aside.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter until tender; spoon evenly over bread.
Top with ham. Combine cheeses and flour; sprinkle over ham.
Combine milk and and next 3 ingredients; pour over cheese.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and let stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: Combine flour, poppy seed, salt and baking soda.
Set aside. In a larger bowl beat sugar and butter until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and lemon peel.
Add the flour mixture and yogurt to the beaten sugar mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: no bake fresh blueberry pie(yield: one 9-inch pie)
directions: In a small bowl, make a smooth paste of water, flour and salt. Set aside. In a saucepan, boil 1 cup blueberries, sugar and 1/2 cup water. Reduce heat and slowly add flour paste and stir until thick. Remove from heat and set aside to cool to lukewarm. When cool, gently add remaining 3 cups of blueberries. Blend gently and pour into pie shell. Refrigerate. When cold, garnish with whipped topping and serve.

title: lit'l cornbread wraps
directions: Separate dough into 16 strips.
Cut each strip in half.
Wrap dough around Lit'l Links and press ends together to seal.
Bake as directed on dough package.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: In medium bowl combine chopped chicken, bean sprouts, water chestnuts and green onion; set aside.
In a custard cup stir together soy sauce, vinegar, sesame oil and pepper.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Toss well.
Cover and chill.

title: lois' green salad
directions: Mix first two ingredients and let cool.
Add cottage cheese and mayonnaise.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill until set.
Serve on lettuce.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Combine the biscuit mix, sugar and cinnamon in a mixing bowl. Stir in nuts, cherries (with the liquid) and egg.
Blend well. Turn into greased and floured 1 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool before slicing.

title: 20 minute apple butter
directions: Boil 20 minutes and put in prepared jars.

title: fried summer squash
directions: Roll sliced squash in corn bread mix.
Fry in butter or margarine.

title: hawaiian delight cake
directions: Mix and bake yellow cake mix according to directions.
Mix pineapple with sugar and let simmer while cake is baking.
When cake is done- poke holes in cake with fork, lots of holes.
Pour pineapple mixture over cake and let cool.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Coat chicken with mix.
(There will be mix left in bowl, save it.)
Coat baking pan with no-stick spray.
Pour water in pan.
Arrange chicken (meaty side up).
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken. Pour wine over chicken evenly.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 15 minutes on 325°.
Remove foil from pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, lay foil on the bottom of the pan.
Beat eggs in a small bowl, bread crumbs and butter in separate dishes.
Coat chicken by first dipping each piece in egg, then bread crumbs.
Lay chicken in baking pan.
Pour butter over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour with foil on, remove foil and bake 15 minutes for each side or until chicken is brown.
Remove from pan and pour any remaining butter on chicken and serve.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix ingredients together by hand.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes until center is golden.
Cool 1 minute on sheet and then remove to rack.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple, then dissolve Jell-O and cool.
Add buttermilk and fold in whipped topping.
Refrigerate.
May be served with chopped nuts and/or coconut.

title: sand dabs
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and vanilla and blend.
Add flour, mixing thoroughly.
Add nuts (pecans recommended).
Roll a tablespoonful into a ball.
Place on slightly oiled baking sheet. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: winner's nutrition salad
directions: Wash and thinly slice the tomatoes.
Grate onions, carrots and radishes.
Shred cabbage and lettuce.
Slice green pepper thin and sprinkle the bean sprouts.
Mix all the vegetables and toss lightly in Italian dressing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut in small pieces.
Mix with mayonnaise. Melt oleo and mix with cracker crumbs. Layer 1/2 in large casserole and save rest for top.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour on top of crumbs, then put the other crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Mix the sugar, flour and baking soda by hand.
Add the eggs, then add the other ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: mary's garlic cheese ball
directions: Place a piece of foil wrap about 18 inches long onto counter top; place a piece of plastic wrap the same size over the foil. Leave these in place while you prepare the cheese ball.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Bake uncovered at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: elegant potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes according to package.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: no peek stew
directions: Put stewing beef in roaster or covered casserole.
Arrange carrot, onion and potato pieces with chopped celery on meat.
Mix tomato juice, cornstarch, sugar, salt, pepper and A.1. sauce and then pour over meat and vegetables.
Seal tightly with foil or cover.
Bake at 300° for 4 to 5 hours.
Last 15 minutes, arrange canned biscuits on top and bake, covered, 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: homemade corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Roll wieners in mixture.
Drop in deep fat fryer of hot oil.
Let fry till golden brown.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: Mix all together;
press mixture in bottom and 3/4 ways up side in a 9-inch pie pan or 10 x 13-inch pan, saving 1/3 cup for later.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight before serving with vegetables.

title: cool hawaiian dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place paper baking cups in muffin tins. Fill with mixture and freeze until firm. Serves 20. Delicious!

title: ham balls
directions: Mix ingredients and form into balls.

title: dried beef and noodles
directions: Mix the mushroom soup with 1 cup of cheese.
Mix with the dried beef, noodles and peas.
Make the night before.
Put in a casserole dish and refrigerate.
The next day, sprinkle sharp Cheddar cheese over the top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend egg with vinegar and water.
Cut
Crisco into flour; toss with fork while gradually adding the liquid mixture.
Roll out and place in single pan or a double crust pie.

title: limeade
directions: Mix together in pitcher and stir well.
Serve cold.

title: milner applesauce
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Cook in a covered pot with water for 15 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.
Remove from heat; add sugar and cinnamon.
Cool.

title: american fried rice
directions: Rice:
Place rice and 4 cups of water in a pot.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until the water is gone.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix in a baking dish corn, muffin mix, oil, eggs and garlic salt.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Then divide dough in half and wrap each mound in waxed paper.
Chill for several hours in refrigerator.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease or line 12 muffins cups. In large bowl stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. In a separate bowl, combine milk, bananas, egg and margarine. Add banana mixture to flour mixture and combine just until moistened. Fold in chopped walnuts.
Spoon evenly into muffin cups. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.

title: fish fillet
directions: Soak fish fillets in buttermilk 2 to 3 hours with lemon rind on	top.
Drain. Mix pancake mix and club soda, then dip floured fillets
in
the
mix
and deep fry in 1 1/2 pints hot vegetable oil for about 4 minutes on each side.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese and mix in a mixer.
Add rest of ingredients. Chill 2 hours.
Shape into 1 large ball or 2 small balls.
Roll in pecans.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk and mix well.
Pour into 1 gallon ice cream freezer container and fill with whole milk to fill line, or about 3/4 full.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
(For basic vanilla ice cream, omit the strawberry flavoring, pie filling and fresh strawberries and increase vanilla to 2 tablespoons.)

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cook chicken in water with salt, pepper, and garlic salt until tender.
Cool and remove bones.
Mix shortening and enough flour to make a thick paste together.
Cook over medium heat until dark brown.
Stir frequently.
Add vegetables.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables stand away from roux (flour mixture). Return chicken to broth and bring to a boil.
Drop roux by spoonfuls into boiling chicken and broth.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except broccoli, in 2-quart pan. Stir until cornstarch is dissolved.
Add broccoli; cook on medium until broccoli is tender, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with broccoli florets.

title: fruit-nut-white chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter, brown sugar and vanilla in large bowl until creamy.
Beat in egg. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chips, nuts and fruit bits.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients, reserving 1 cup tomato sauce. Spoon mixture into 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes. Heat reserved tomato sauce and serve with meat loaf. Makes 6 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cut bacon into tiny pieces and fry.
Drain kidney and butter beans.
Mix it all together and bake in an uncovered casserole dish at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs.
Place all in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aldrich family clams casino
directions: Melt together butter, lemon juice, garlic powder, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Add liquid to crackers.
Mix. Put spoonful on top of each little neck.
Add 2-inch slice of bacon.
Broil until bacon is done.

title: golden bacon cornbread
directions: Blend cornmeal, milk and sour cream together.
Set aside for 30 minutes.
Add beaten egg to mixture.
Blend dry ingredients into batter, just until smooth.
Add bacon.
Bake at 400° in greased and floured pan for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: french market bean soup
directions: Use heavy 5-quart pot to cook bean mixture in 2 1/2 quarts water.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer.
While beans are cooking, make very small meat balls from sausage meat, ground beef, onion, salt and peppers.
Fry or bake in oven to brown and remove excess fat.
After beans have cooked for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, add browned meat balls and cook for 30 minutes.
Then add potatoes, carrots, tomatoes, tomato paste, salt and peppers.
Cook an additional 20 minutes or until all ingredients are done.
Add lemon juice and serve.

title: birds in nest breakfast
directions: Take a slice of bread.
Cut a center out of bread with a small round cutter.
Place bread in greased hot frypan or griddle. Break an egg in the center of the slice of bread.
Fry, flip and fry.
The leftover rounds can be fried also.
Serve hot with jam or jelly.

title: broccoli or cauliflower casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and heat in microwave.
Cook vegetable; drain and mix in sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. During last 10 minutes, crush 1 sleeve of Ritz crackers on top. Sprinkle with seasoned salt and dab with butter.

title: chicken brunswick stew
directions: Before going to bed at night, put whole chicken, potatoes, onion and tomatoes into slow cooker.
Cook all night on low.
In morning, remove chicken from pot and take away all bones.
Return meat to pot and add ketchup, barbecue sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook all day or until ready to eat.
Add corn, salt and pepper.

title: scottish scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in butter. Stir in milk to make a soft dough. Divide into 2 round portions. Cut each round into 4 wedges. Place on baking sheet. Brush with milk. Bake at 400° for 12-15 minutes. Serve warm with preserves.

title: cheddar sesame garden vegetables
directions: In small saucepan, whisk small amount of milk into flour. Stir in mustard.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Serve over vegetables.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds. Makes 2 servings.

title: flag cake
directions: Slice 1 cup strawberries, set aside.
Halve remaining strawberries; set aside.
Line bottom of 9 X 13 inch dish with cake slices.
Top with sliced strawberries and 1 cup blueberries. Spread whipped topping evenly over berries.
Arrange strawberry halves and remaining 1/3 cup blueberries on whipped topping to create a flag design.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 15 servings.

title: susan's biscuits
directions: Melt margarine/butter.
Mix all three ingredients together. Bake at 350° until brown in miniature muffin pans.

title: chocolate chips
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients to flour mixture.
Mix and if dry, add 1/2 cup warm water.
Add one 12 ounce package chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 15 to 20 dozen.

title: baked tomato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a baking dish.
Top with small amount of butter, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cheese and onion quiche
directions: Mix
cracker
crumbs
and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Press evenly into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in about 2 tablespoons butter (tender, not brown).
Spread onions over crumb crust.
Scald milk and pour over slightly beaten eggs.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole (leftover peas or other vegetable may be added).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: granola
directions: Mix all together, except fruit.
Bake in a 325° oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in fruit and spread mix out to cool.
Very good!

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: Saute celery, carrot and onion in butter.
Add tomatoes, basil and Parmesan.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Put in crock-pot before bed.
Set on high until hot, then turn to low.
When you get up turn on high.
Stir occasionally until thick.
Can as desired; seal in jars.

title: italian ziti medley
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, brown sausage; remove from pan and drain off fat.
Melt butter and cook mushrooms, pepper and onion until tender, but not brown.
Blend flour into vegetable mixture. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium-low heat until mixture begins to boil.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Blend in 1 1/2 cups of Cheddar cheese, Parmesan cheese and pepper until cheeses are melted and mixture is smooth.
Cook ziti according to package; drain.
Stir hot ziti and sausage into vegetable cheese mixture.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump pineapple in pan (do not drain) and spread.
Put pie filling over pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix over pie filling.
Cut oleo or margarine and spread out over entire pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Divide chicken, green pepper, onion and cheese between pie shells.
Top each with 1 tablespoon flour and 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour half into each shell.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: belgian waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar in a bowl until light.
Add cooled, melted margarine, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and then gently fold into batter.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes in Belgian waffle iron.

title: coconut snowball
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 350°.
With electric mixer, beat margarine until creamy.
Gradually beat in sugar. Add vanilla.
On
sheet of foil, stir together flour and salt. Add
to butter mixture, blending well.
Form dough into 1-inch balls (if too soft, refrigerate for 2 hours).
Roll in flaked coconut and place
on
prepared
cookie
sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: curried chicken with couscous(low-fat, heart healthy)
directions: You will also need Pam or other cooking spray.

title: spicy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars and eggs.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Mix all ingredients only until blended.
Shape dough into 2 rolls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm.
To bake, cut rolls into 1/4-inch slices. Bake on greased baking sheet in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on wire racks.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.
Will stay fresh up to 2 weeks if stored airtight.

title: green onion cheese spread
directions: Prepare about 30 minutes before serving or day ahead.
In small bowl, beat all ingredients with mixer at low speed until light and fluffy.
Serve with crackers or party bread slices. Yields 2 cups.

title: easy tomato sauce
directions: Cook onions in stock until soft.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 3 (1 1/2 cups).

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: lemon pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together and cook in double boiler.
When thickness results, remove from heat and cool.
Pour into baked pie shell; cover with meringue.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute the sausage, onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic in skillet with a little oil.
Add beans, tomatoes, wine and spices and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over cooked rice.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in oleo, dip and coat with mixture of remaining ingredients. Bake on greased (Pam) medium pan or foil-lined pan. Bake at 400 degrees about 30 minutes.

title: harriett gill's pineapple fluff pie
directions: Bring pineapple, water and 1/3 cup sugar to a boil.
Mix cornstarch to a paste with a little water and add.
Cook until mixture is thick and clear.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks and return to heat for another minute.
Cool slightly.
Add lemon juice, salt and stiffly beaten egg whites, to which remaining sugar has been added.
Pour into baked pastry and chill in refrigerator until set.
Top with whipped cream for serving.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Put first four ingredients into a 8-quart kettle with 2 c. water.
Boil 15 min.
Add 2 c. tomato juice, ground beef, cheese. Cook 5 min. longer or until cheese melts.
Mix 1/4 c. flour and 1/2 c. water as thickening.
Add to kettle of soup.
Let cook until veggies are soft.
Stir often, then add milk.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve.
Make 5 quarts.
Delicious!

title: sweet potato casserole ii
directions: Wash sweet potatoes; peel and slice into a pan. Add water and boil until tender. Drain and mash. Add remaining ingredients and mix. Put into a baking dish and prepare topping.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts, then break chicken into small pieces. Grate pickles, celery, boiled eggs, onion and green pepper.
Put all this together.
Add salt and pepper, then add mayonnaise. Stir, making sure to mix well.

title: wine welcomer
directions: Stir together orange juice, lemonade and wine in large container.
Add club soda just before serving.
Serve in wine glasses over crushed ice.
Garnish with orange slices.
Yields 10 1/2 cups.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fifteen minutes before serving:
Preheat broiler.
Cut stems from mushrooms.
Gently toss mushrooms in melted butter.
Place mushrooms cut end up in broiler pan.
Broil 3 minutes.
Meanwhile in small bowl, combine cheese and bread crumbs.
Spoon some of cheese mixture into each mushroom.
Top with olive slice.
Return to oven and broil 3 to 5 minutes until cheese is melted and mushrooms are tender.
Can also use American or Cheddar cheese.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and refrigerate 24 hours. Mix again before serving.
Makes a large bowl of salad.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with cut pieces of fruit: grapes, apple wedges, etc.

title: mom's noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles for 5 minutes; drain and cool. When noodles are cooled, add all the ingredients. Put 1/2 cup oil in a small frying pan and heat. When oil is hot, add mixture, medium heat. When noodles are golden brown, flip the pudding. Cook the other side until it is brown.

title: beef vegetable dish
directions: Brown beef with onions in skillet.
Stir in tomato, vegetable soup and water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer while preparing biscuits.
Mix flour and shortening into coarse crumbs. Stir in Italian seasonings and blend in enough milk to make into a batter.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls in mixture.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes until biscuits are golden brown.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Drain and rinse sauerkraut.
Layer sauerkraut, corned beef, cheese and dressing.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serve with dark rye bread.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar; put eggs in one at a time, and cream. Add pumpkin and flour with cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add raisins, dates and nuts last.
Bake 55 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and nutmeg with a fork until thoroughly blended.
Add evaporated milk and blend again.
Slice bread approximately 3/4-inch thick and soak (submerge) each slice for about a minute.
Fry in butter or margarine at medium heat, taking care not to burn it.
Serve with butter or margarine and maple syrup.
Serves 4.

title: fast banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in mashed bananas and eggs.
Add Bisquick mix and nuts.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Cool before serving.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Drain clams and reserve liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to measure 3 cups.
Partially cook bacon; add celery and onion.
Cook and stir until vegetables are tender.
Cut up tomatoes.
Stir in clam juice and water, undrained chopped tomatoes, potatoes, carrots and seasonings.
Boil and them reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Mash vegetables slightly.
Add clams.
Turn into covered casserole and refrigerate 3 to 24 hours before serving.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, pumpkin, egg and vanilla. Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: In large bowl mix cooked rice, cooked broccoli and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Spread Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chili cheese appetizer
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend together. Add melted butter, chilies and cottage cheese and mix until blended.
Pour into buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, or until test with knife blade comes out clean.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting into small serving pieces.

title: pacific lime mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add juice from pineapple and chill until thick.
Add pineapple, cheese, mayonnaise and nuts.
Mix and return to refrigerator to chill until firm.

title: kentucky beaten biscuits
directions: Work lard into dry ingredients until consistency of coarse corn meal. Add liquid, very little at a time, until dough is very stiff. Add as little of the liquid as possible. The stiffer the dough, the better the biscuits. Roll dough until satiny smooth. Cut biscuits about 1/2-inch thick. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a ball. Cover with nuts.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour oil in large mixing bowl. Add sugar and eggs. Beat until creamy. Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add small amount of flour mixture to creamy mixture. When all flour mixture has been used, fold in apples and nuts. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream until light 1 pound margarine and 3 cups sugar.
Add and beat well 6 eggs.
Alternately add 4 cups flour, milk, vanilla extract and almond extract.
After all ingredients are combined, beat at high speed one minute.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch pan 2 hours at 300°.
Cool pan.
Do not invert pan.

title: spinach mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes with butter.
Add other ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese on top in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves about 10.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated, then it may need to be baked longer to heat through.

title: nanny's candy pie
directions: Blend sugar and butter well.
Blend in chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend well.
Pour into a saucepan and heat until sugar is fully melted.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and refrigerate.
Enjoy.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cube steak and brown in a small amount of oil in a large skillet. Mix undiluted soups with salt and pepper; pour over meat. Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours, until meat is tender. Stir in sour cream and sliced mushrooms. Serve over cooked rice or noodles. Sprinkle parsley flakes on top.

title: pennsylvania dutch shoo-fly pie
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Mix flour, sugar and shortening together with hands to make crumbs.
Take out 1/3 cup of crumbs for top.
Be sure water is boiling; add molasses.
Take off heat. Dissolve soda in vinegar and add to molasses and water; pour into crumbs.
Mix until smooth.
Put into unbaked pastry shell. Sprinkle the 1/3 cup of crumbs over top.
This makes one 9-inch pie.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes; it is done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Pour in rice.
Stir in soups (undiluted), broccoli and Cheez Whiz.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: soda cracker dessert
directions: Beat egg whites to points.
Add sugar gradually while you continue beating.
Add crackers which have been crushed by hand. Add nuts, vanilla and baking powder.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: tofu and brown rice(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat a large skillet or wok and coat with 2 teaspoons oil and the butter.
Add onion and saute until lightly browned.
Add brown rice, then tofu, sauteing each for 2 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place tofu/onion mixture in casserole or bread pan coated with remaining oil.
Pour in the milk; sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Make 10 helpings of instant mashed potatoes (follow directions on the box).
Mix together the cream cheese, sour cream and garlic salt.
Stir into potatoes.
Melt half stick of butter.
Pour over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: beef and vegetable fried rice
directions: In large, nonstick skillet, brown beef, garlic and ginger over medium heat, 8 to 10 minutes or until no longer pink.
Remove beef, put oil in skillet,
stir-fry pepper and pea pods until crisp-tender.
Add rice, soy sauce and sesame oil.
Mix well. Return beef to mixture and heat through, about 5 minutes.
Stir in green onion, if desired.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt butter.
In oven, sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool. Chill and cut into bars.
Store at room temperature.

title: frosted chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Add vanilla and melted semi-sweet chocolate.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add to the first mixture alternately with the sour milk.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost with Powdered Sugar Frosting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in 2 cups water.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat and cool until meat can be removed from bones.
Cook rice in the chicken liquid.
Cut chicken in bite-size pieces.
In large casserole, place layer of rice, layer of meat, and 1 can of gravy.
Use remaining rice and gravy.
Top with bread crumbs that have been mixed with 1/2 stick margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins until water is absorbed.
Cool.
Mix shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs, then dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts (extra flour will make the cookies keep their nice round shape).
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon meringue pie 2
directions: Beat the Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and egg yolks together. Pour into a baked pie shell.
Add the meringue (beat egg whites, sugar and vanilla until stiff peaks form).
Place in the oven and bake on 325° until meringue turns light brown.

title: punch juice
directions: Chill the above ingredients and mix together.
Add 2 trays of ice cubes and serve.

title: spicy monterey rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, combine water, rice and bouillon; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup Colby cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 3 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal pudding cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, pudding mix and margarine.
Add eggs and blend well.
Then add the dry ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mulligatawny soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes, until vegetables are cooked.
Stir occasionally.
Remove cloves before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Serve with crisp French bread or breadsticks, if desired.

title: swedish cream
directions: In a saucepan, mix together the cream, sugar and gelatin. Heat the mixture over low heat until the sugar is dissolved, about 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Top with croutons.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through entirely.

title: pork medallions in creamy leek sauce
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Brown pork medallions after seasoning lightly with garlic powder.
Place in baking dish.
Mix leek soup with water.
Pour over pork slices.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° until done.
Serve with rice or potatoes and vegetables.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach in salted water.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Add flour and stir.
Add milk; cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add spinach, eggs, chopped onions, nutmeg, salt and red or white pepper to taste.
Pour into a baking dish.
Top with grated cheese, then crumbs on top of cheese.
Dot with 3 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: layered fresh salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in order.
Mix together mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and sugar.
Spread on top.
Top with crumbled bacon, eggs and tomatoes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil rotini until just cooked, but not too soft.
Rinse in cold water.
Combine pasta with chopped green pepper, olives, dressing and 1/2 bottle of Salad Supreme.
Mix and chill.

title: springerle(cookies)
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
In separate bowl, beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and anise seed.
Mix well.
Add lemon peel and flour mixture.
Mix well.
Chill one hour or until firm enough to handle.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Use springerle mold or your favorite cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet 1/2-inch apart and leave exposed to air overnight.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 30 minutes or until done.
Store covered. Best to wait three weeks before serving.
Will keep for months. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: grape jelly
directions: Combine grape and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 4 minutes.
Soak gelatine in cold water.
When dissolved, add to hot grape juice.
When cool, pour into small jars and refrigerate.
This is about 14 or 15 calories per tablespoon.

title: mock oyster rockerfeller
directions: Boil chopped broccoli and drain.
Saute onion in butter until soft.
Combine soup, onion and mushrooms and mix with broccoli and crumbled cheese in pan.
Heat on low until cheese melts.
Add almonds and stir well.
Serve hot in chafing dish as a cocktail dip with Melba toast or your favorite cracker.
Serves 25.
As a vegetable casserole, bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot and bubbling.
Serves 8.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add mayonnaise and mix well.
Mix soda into warm water and add to the flour mixture.
Mix well and add the vanilla.
Don't overbeat.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes or until sides pull away from pan.

title: strawberry icing
directions: Cream butter until smooth; gradually blend in 3 cups of sugar and salt, adding strawberry juice and cream from time to time to produce a smooth spreading consistency.
Spread on cakes, serving out part of the icing.
Add rest of sugar to make the mixture stiff enough to hold its slices of strawberry.
Enough icing for 2 (8-inch) layers or 16 small cupcakes.

title: pierogies
directions: Mix flour with salt.
Add egg and water.
Knead lightly. Cover dough with towel and set aside.
Saute onion in vegetable oil; mash potatoes.
Add onion to potatoes and mix well.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cool.
Roll dough thin.
Cut into rounds with water glass.
Hold round in palm of hand; place spoonful of filling in center.
Fold in half.
Press edges to seal; place on dry towel and cover.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Mix with pork, beef, onion and seasonings.
Knead well. Shape into balls and brown in pan on top of stove.
Place in roasting pan. Add water to drippings in frying pan. Scrape loose any browned bits of meat and pour this over the meatballs in the roaster. Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Add potato water to broth and thicken with cornstarch for gravy.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil, beating well.
Next, add plums and continue beating.
Mix dry ingredients together and add gradually to wet mixture.
Add chopped nuts last and pour into a well-greased tube or loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Ice with caramel icing if desired.

title: crabmeat potato chip casserole
directions: Melt butter, in saucepan, over low heat.
Stir in flour and celery salt.
Add milk gradually; stir until thickened and smooth. Stir in mayonnaise.

title: beef stroganoff(crock-pot)
directions: Brown meat in oil with salt and pepper; drain; put in crock-pot with rest of ingredients except wine and sour cream. Cook on low heat for 8 to 10 hours.
To serve, turn to high heat setting until bubbly; blend in wine and sour cream; cook another 15 minutes.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix cottage cheese with Jell-O. Drain pineapple and mix with cottage cheese mixture, then blend in Cool Whip. Keep cool in refrigerator.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or wok over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms, onions and ginger.
Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Push vegetables aside; pour egg into skillet and scramble.
Stir in rice, gently separating grains.
Add shrimp and soy sauce; stir until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving is 189 calories.

title: judy milliken's grandma law gumdrop cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed ingredients. Add remaining ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 6 dozen.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir well and chill.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Boil in salted water until tender; drain.
Brown onions in 1/2 stick butter.
In casserole dish, combine eggplant, 1 cup grated cheese, onions and soup mix; mix well.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Pour remaining butter over cracker crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: bill's south of the border salsa dip
directions: Over medium heat, add beer to Cheddar cheese.
Stir until thick and creamy.
No lumps!
Add chunky salsa; chop jalapeno pepper and add to mixture.
Stir over heat for 5 to 10 minutes. Serve in bowl with tortilla chips!

title: enhanced banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add egg and beat well. Stir in lemon juice and bananas.
Stir in flour, baking powder and soda that have been mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in loaf pan, depending on your oven.

title: mareta's party cheese ball
directions: Combine all cheese, Worcestershire sauce, onion or garlic and olives; blend thoroughly with an electric mixer until smooth. Chill overnight.
Form into a ball with your hands.
Roll 1/2 of the ball in chopped walnuts and other half in minced parsley. Arrange walnut halves around center of cheese ball.
Serve on a tray with assorted crackers and pretzel sticks.

title: taco munch
directions: In large bowl, combine popcorn, cereal and pretzels.
Combine butter and taco seasoning and drizzle over mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cool completely and store in airtight container.
Serve with Cheddar cheese squares.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with milk.
Put a layer of graham crackers on bottom of casserole. Spread half of pudding on top.
Spread half of Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Put a layer of graham crackers on top.
Repeat layers again of pudding, Cool Whip and graham crackers. Spread fudge icing on top. Better when fixed a day in advance. Can freeze and serve partially frozen.

title: marinated pork roast
directions: Make marinade. Place roast in a large plastic bag and pour marinade over it. Close bag and refrigerate overnight. Remove meat from marinade. Place on rack in shallow roasting pan. Roast, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Baste occasionally with the reserved marinade during the last hour of cooking. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: kansas cream style corn for freezer
directions: Mix and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool.
Put in containers for freezer and freeze.
Add salt, pepper or sugar to taste when heating to serve.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cut cake into 3 even layers, set aside. Mix together in large bowl; crushed pineapple (drained) vanilla instant pudding and cool whip mixture. Place layer of cake on plate, with cool whip mixture. Place 2nd layer on first and cover top and sides with cool whip mixture. Place 3rd layer on 2nd layer and cover top and sides of entire cake, continue to cover until all cool whip mixture has been used. Refrigerate till ready to eat.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put cream of chicken soup and milk in casserole dish.
Stir well.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Put water and butter in bowl and stir until butter has melted.
Add stuffing and stir until moist.
Spoon stuffing mixture on top of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs (well beaten). Add milk alternately with flour, baking soda and baking powder. Add creamed bananas. Add vanilla. Bake 40 minutes

title: lace cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line baking sheet with foil; melt butter. Grind pecans (1 cup) and sugar in food processor.
Combine nut mixture, flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat together butter, vanilla and egg; stir into flour mixture.
Mix well and divide batter into thirds.
Chop cherries and raisins; stir into 1/3 of mix along with oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 3 inches apart. Bake about 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Drop next 1/3 of mix by teaspoonfuls.
Flatten slightly and place a pecan half on top. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Drop remaining 1/3 of mix by teaspoon about 5 inches apart; flatten slightly.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and drizzle melted chocolate over tops of plain cookies or all.

title: crowd pleaser potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes (with skins on) until tender.
Cool thoroughly. Peel and grate potatoes.
Add butter to soup and warm until melted. Remove from heat.
Add to soup sour cream, green onions, salt and pepper.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer potatoes, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat twice.
Top with remaining cheese (1/2 cup in reserve).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves approximately 15 to 20.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam; arrange chicken breasts in bottom.
Salt and pepper. Drain sauerkraut slightly and place over chicken.
Cover with Swiss cheese slices, pour dressing over cheese and cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 275°.
Do not open foil during baking.

title: dry peaches
directions: Pour sugar over peaches.
Let set 3 hours or overnight.
Pour vinegar over them. Cook very slowly until they are dry. Stir constantly.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add butter and milk.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat with hand held mixer.
Put in buttered 8-inch square dish.
Refrigerate.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Fry butter, broccoli and onion in skillet, slowly, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz and milk; mix well.
Mix in rice; simmer or bake.
Serves 12.
Great for covered dish dinners.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Spread macaroni and cheese in baking dish (9 x 9-inch).
Mix prepared hamburger with pizza sauce and pour over top of macaroni. Top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or microwave until thoroughly warm.

title: chili cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into roll.
Roll in chili powder. Chill until firm.
Serve on crackers.

title: chili potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Empty potatoes into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cook and stir ground beef, green pepper, onion and salt in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown.
Drain.
Stir in sauce mix, chili powder, water and beans.
Stir into potatoes. Cover and bake until potatoes are tender, about 40 minutes. Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Combine flour with salt in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture is the size of small peas.
Sprinkle water, a little at a time, over mixture while tossing and stirring lightly with a fork.
Add water to driest particles, pushing lumps to side until dough is just moist enough to hold together.
Form into a ball. Flatten into 1/2-inch thickness; smooth edge.
Roll out on floured surface 1 1/2 times the size of the inverted pie plate, 9-inch. Fit loosely into pan.
Fold edge to form a standing rim.
Flute.

title: eagle brand ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in freezer and freeze.
Can add peaches, strawberries or whatever if desired.

title: squash hush puppies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls in deep hot oil.

title: glorified pasta salad
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until brown.
Add the next 6 ingredients.
Simmer until thick, then add mustard and ketchup.

title: aunt doris nitchen's lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix together and spread.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Pound flank steak with mallet until 3/4-inch thick.
Spread dressing mixture over all.
Roll up as jelly roll.
Tie securely in several places.
Brown in butter in Dutch oven.
Add beef stock.
Cover.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Thicken gravy. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix rice with mushroom soup in casserole dish.
Add milk to mixture.
Place chicken breasts on top of mixture.
Pour dried Lipton soup on top of chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for one hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Combine oil, eggs and sugar; mix well.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir until all ingredients are moistened.
Stir in strawberries and pecans.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove to wire rack and cool completely.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: old timey syllabub
directions: Combine apple juice, sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Using a whisk, gently fold in whipping cream until frothy and well combined.
Serve immediately or refrigerate, covered, several hours or overnight.
Cream will rise to top of mixture.
Whisk again before serving.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serves 12.

title: baked french toast
directions: Prepared the night before,
it's
ready
to serve in no time. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheeseball
directions: Combine all ingredients (except pecans) and shape into a ball. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: ryan's ginger cookies
directions: Mix well, roll in balls.
Dip in sugar and flatten with fork. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tortilla bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a medium skillet, cook beef and onion until beef is brown and crumbly (about 10 minutes). Drain well.
Add enchilada and tomato sauces to skillet; stir well.
Cook until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
Spoon beef mixture into a 2 quart baking dish.
In a separate small bowl, combine beans and evaporated milk. Then, spread over beef mixture.
Arrange whole tortilla chips around the edge of baking dish. Top casserole with crushed chips. Sprinkle cheeses over the top.
Bake casserole until hot and bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: grandma's white fruitcake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt, then add to the butter mixture alternately with flour and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Flour all fruit and add to mixture.
Add almond flavoring.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until done.

title: cheesecake
directions: In a spring-form pan, pour melted butter over graham cracker crumbs forming a crust in pan and around the sides.
In a bowl, mix eggs and sugar until well blended.
Add cream cheese and vanilla. Continue to mix until well blended.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Wait to cool and pour favorite topping (e.g., Comstock Cherry Pie Filling).

title: *bumsteads
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into hot dog buns.
Place in a 350° oven until cheese melts.
Serves 8.

title: frozen salad dessert
directions: Fold pie filling and pineapple together.
Gently stir in milk; fold in Cool Whip until well blended.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cover with foil and refrigerate.
Can be frozen.
Keeps for a long time in freezer.
Also good with peaches, blueberries or strawberries.

title: shrimp and scallop gratin
directions: In a bowl combine the shrimp and scallops.
Divide the mixture among 4 well-buttered 5-inch gratin dishes and sprinkle each dish with sherry.
Mince together the parsley and garlic and in a bowl combine the mixture with scallion and oregano.
Stir in bread crumbs, salt, cayenne and pepper.
Sprinkle the mixture over the seafood and drizzle it with butter.
Bake the dishes in the upper third of a preheated hot oven (400°) for 12 minutes or until the tops are browned.
Serves 4.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with apples.
Let stand for sugar to dissolve, approximately 2 hours.
Pack into sterilized quart jars.
Seal and process in hot water bath for 50 minutes. Yields 7 quarts.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and peanut butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoons on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and serve with crackers.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt ingredients in a skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Mix into the popcorn.
Put caramel corn into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 275° for 3/4 to 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until done, then add oil, vinegar, eggs, onion, pickles, mustard and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Use hot or refrigerate.

title: chocolate mint dessert
directions: Beat egg whites and 2 tablespoons powdered sugar until stiff. Cream oleo, 2 cups powdered sugar, melted chocolate and egg yolks until light and fluffy.
Fold whites into creamed mixture.
Spread onto crumb and oleo crust; freeze.
Soften ice cream and spread over frozen mixture.

title: chocolate peanut butter brownies
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and unsweetened chocolate over low heat.
Beat eggs until light and pale colored.
Add eggs, sugar and flour to chocolate mixture.
Cook for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers, sugar and vinegar in pot. Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes. Add Certo and boil for 1 more minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal. Can use green or red food coloring.

title: reese's cake squares
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking soda; set aside.
In saucepan, mix margarine, cocoa, butter and water. Bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix with spoon.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool; top with peanut butter.

title: wheat germ snack ring
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Sprinkle extra wheat germ over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Don't let the name fool you; even your kids will love this.

title: glugg
directions: Cover raisins with 3 cups water.
Add spices and cracked cardamon seeds and shells.
Simmer covered for 2 hours.
Remove from heat; add wine.
Bring almost to a simmer (160°) for 2 hours. Leave overnight.
Drain.
Squeeze raisins to get all wine out. Put in bottles.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Beat softened cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice. Pour into pie crust.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Put all ingredients in double boiler and beat with electric mixer for 7 minutes or until mixture stand in stiff peaks.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and spread on cake.

title: chicken with cranberries
directions: In a saucepan, mix cranberries, onion, orange juice, ginger and cinnamon; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour mixture over chicken breasts that have been placed in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until chicken is very tender.

title: san francisco fettucini
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add garlic, clams, parsley, soup and white cooking wine to taste until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream and Parmesan cheese to taste; pour over fettucini.
Serve with a nice salad and French bread.

title: baked parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into quarters (thick slices).
Combine flour, cheese, salt, pepper and parsley in bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake in bag, coating potatoes well with cheese mixture.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place potatoes in layer in pan.
Bake at 375°
for 1 hour.

title: date loaf
directions: In large bowl, cut dates in small pieces and put soda over them. Add boiling water. When cool, add beaten egg. Add sugar and other ingredients. Mix and pour into 9-inch loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oxtail stew
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender. Boil oxtails until tender, very tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer until thick, for about 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oven chicken
directions: Wrap each breast in dried beef and bacon strips.
Use toothpicks to hold together.
Place in a large Pyrex baking dish. Combine sour cream and soup (undiluted).
Pour over top of chicken. Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 300°.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix all ingredients; mash fine with fork and roll into a ball. Serve with party bread.
(Best if made day ahead.)

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 (9-inch) baked pie crusts and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Form into small balls and roll in lightly beaten egg whites, then roll in chopped nuts.
Bake 5 minutes in a 350° oven.
Take out and thumbprint each cookie.
Return to oven.
Bake 8 minutes more.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Lightly beat eggs.
Melt butter. Combine all ingredients and form into balls or patties.
Freeze or bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until browned.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix together.
Butter bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer graham crackers on bottom. Spread 1/2 of pudding mix, then another layer of graham crackers.
Put remaining pudding mix on, then another layer of graham crackers.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, water, oil and gelatin.
Blend
in the eggs.
Stir in the strawberries.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) cake tins or 1 Bundt pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool on racks.

title: grapefruit, red onion and avocado salad
directions: Cut grapefruit sections into 3 pieces.
Toss avocados with all but 2 tablespoons juice reserved from grapefruit.
Whisk together mayonnaise, remaining 2 tablespoons grapefruit juice and lemon juice.
Season with salt and pepper.
Line 4 plates with lettuce. Drain avocados and toss with grapefruit.
Divide grapefruit mixture among plates.
Top with onion.
Drizzle with dressing and serve.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use cake mix; follow directions substituting 1 1/3 cup pineapple juice for water in batter.
Bake in jelly roll pan for 15 minutes or golden brown.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift together sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening and add brown sugar.
Let cool slightly before beating in eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted mixture, then nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla. Blend well.
Pour into greased pan about 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool, cut into squares.

title: marjorie's cheesecake
directions: Important:
Do not substitute egg product for whole eggs.
Do not use soft cream cheese.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together and store in an airtight jar.
Use 2 to 3 spoonfuls to 1 cup of hot water.

title: christmas cranberry pudding
directions: In one bowl, mix boiling water and molasses.
Add flour and soda.
In another bowl, mix the next 4 ingredients and add to first bowl, stirring just until blended.
Put in a well-oiled, covered steaming pan.
Place on a rack in a large, covered pan of simmering water, coming 2/3 of the way up the side.
Steam for about 1 1/2 hours until firm, but moist (water needs to simmer, not boil).
Cool 30 minutes and invert on small plate.
Cool and wrap with Saran.

title: puffy salmon
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer croutons, salmon and cheese.
Combine beaten eggs and remaining ingredients.
Pour over casserole.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Let rest 5 minutes before serving.

title: supreme turkey divan
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, stir salad dressing and flour over low heat until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly over medium heat until thickened.
Add Cheddar cheese and stir until melted.
Layer broccoli and rice in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with half of the sauce.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese.
Top with turkey, remaining sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until sauce is bubbly.

title: battered fried shrimp
directions: Shell shrimp, leaving tail section in; devein.
Cut shrimp through the back, leaving tail attached.
In bowl, mix next 3 ingredients.
Gradually stir in 1/4 cup corn oil until smooth. Pour 1 quart oil into heavy 3-quart saucepan, filling no more than 1/3 full.
Heat oil to 375°.
Dip shrimp into batter to coat.
Add a few shrimp at a time to hot oil.
Fry for 1 to 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add Italian seasoning and garlic salt to taste.
Boil noodles.
Combine all ingredients and cook covered for 30 minutes in oven.

title: christmas waldorf salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot liquid and add sugar, vinegar, lemon juice and salt.
When partially congealed, add cheese mixture.
Blend with the fruit and nuts.
Mold in desired shape.

title: canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Cut garlic in pieces.
Cut tomatoes into quarters.
Then cook garlic and tomatoes until cooked mushy.
Then put through a strainer.
Cut peppers and onions and cook in oil for 30 minutes, then put them through a strainer.
Now mix tomato juice, onion juice, tomato paste, sugar, salt, sweet basil and oregano.
Cook until thick, then pack in jars and seal.
If they don't seal, cool pack for 2 1/2 hours.
One-half bushel tomatoes and 8 small tomato pastes equal 7 quarts sauce.
One bushel tomatoes and 1 gallon tomato paste equals 14 to 18 quarts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla and oil then add other ingredients.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: open-faced peach pie
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients.
Add
Crisco.
Mix into crumbs. Add the
egg;
mix
well.
Put into pie plate.	Arrange sliced peaches on	crust.	Cream
the
sugar and 1 tablespoon oleo or butter; add the
egg.	Mix well; pour over peaches.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: sauteed roma tomatoes
directions: Heat butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add tomatoes; cook 2 to 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring often.
Be careful that skins do not burst.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Use as a garnish or complement to other side dishes.

title: omelet
directions: Take eggs.
Beat up and add salt and pepper in a little milk. Put butter in small skillet, then pour egg mixture in.
Let the sides set up, about 1 minute.
Put a lid on it and let it cook a couple of minutes.
Take lid off.
Put cheese, ham or bacon on one side, then flip the one side over and seal the edges with your spatula.
Let cook until cheese melts.

title: maryland crab bisque
directions: In saucepan melt margarine; add celery and saute 10 minutes. Stir in white sauce mix and add half and half, chicken broth and sherry.
Stir over low heat until soup bubbles and thickens slightly.
Stir in crabmeat and simmer 1 to 2 minutes longer until heated through.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pie dough. Dot with butter.
Layer tomatoes and top with sugar, spices, vinegar, butter and a sprinkling of flour until all ingredients are used.
Vent crust in center of pie.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°. Reduce heat to 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with a wedge of cheese.

title: easy delicious soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix and simmer for 1 hour.
(Can add broken spaghetti or small shells.)
Serve and enjoy.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Combine and mash Jell-O and cream cheese.
Mash in marshmallows, then add water; add and mix pineapple, water and nuts.
Refrigerate until thick.
Whip cream until thick and fold into mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate marshmallow fudge
directions: Put Hershey bar, marshmallow cream and chocolate chips in large bowl and set aside.
Put remaining ingredients (except pecans) in pan and bring to a boil for 7 to 9 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over first mixture and stir until well mixed.
Then add chopped pecans.
Drop or pour into buttered pan before it hardens. Makes 5 to 6 pounds.
Delicious.

title: microwave pecan millionaires
directions: Microwave caramels and evaporated milk on High 3 1/2 to 5 minutes in a microwave-safe bowl.
You may either chop the pecans or leave them whole.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful onto buttered cookie sheet and refrigerate until set.
Melt dipping chocolate in microwave according to package directions.
Dip caramel mixture into chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: light carrot cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, set aside.
Combine brown sugar and next 7 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Stir in dry ingredients and beat at medium speed until well blended.
Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients. Mix all together real good.
Pour into greased coffee cans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Spread apples over bottom of buttered 8 or 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbly mixture over apples. Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugars and oil.
Add pumpkin, eggs and vanilla.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Grease 3 (1 pound) coffee cans and pour mixture into these.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cans.
Delicious and moist.

title: cracklin' cornbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine eggs and milk with dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add cracklings.
Put shortening in skillet and get it hot.
Pour in batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 450° or until brown.

title: old fashion peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk to soft-ball stage.
Add vanilla and peanut butter. Stir until well blended. Turn out in buttered dish.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Grind bologna in food processor.
Add bologna and seasonings to meat.
Add spaghetti sauce, 3 cups cheese and parsley.
Heat until warm.
Spoon on bun halves and top with extra cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Stir all ingredients until well blended.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup and sour cream. Fold in squash and onion. Combine stuffing with butter; spread half of stuffing mix in bottom of casserole dish. Spoon squash mixture on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: miss cook's banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
In a separate bowl, stir together slightly beaten eggs, cooking oil, buttermilk, vanilla extract and mashed banana.
Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients.
Stir with spoon until evenly mixed.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: mackinaw island fudge
directions: Mix milk, butter, sugars and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar.
Beat with a mixer until smooth and thick, about 6 minutes.
Pour into buttered pan and freeze for 20 minutes.
Cut into pieces.
Yields 1 pound.

title: tabouli(lebanese salad)
directions: Slice the parsley, mint and green onions into small pieces. Cut the tomatoes into cubes.
Soak the cracked wheat and mix all of the ingredients together.
Add oil, salt and spices.
Add more salt or lemon if needed.
Serve it with cabbage (wrap and eat). Can be made ahead.
Serves 5.

title: no brown stew
directions: Place meat and vegetables in covered casserole.
Mix soups and Kitchen Bouquet and pour over.
Bake 5 hours in a 250° oven.
Add 1 large can of sliced mushrooms just before removing from oven. Minced garlic and chunks of zucchini are good.
Add some water for more gravy.

title: chocolate angel cake dessert
directions: Break cake into bits.
Place in casserole size dish.
Separate eggs.
Beat the egg whites until they stand in soft peaks.
Place chocolate chips and slightly beaten egg yolks in a saucepan.
Stir the mixture over low heat just until chocolate melts.
Add chocolate mixture to beaten egg whites.
Fold in whipped cream. Pour over the cake bits; stir lightly to mix.
If no munchers are about, dessert keeps well in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook carrots and squash together, about 8 minutes.
Saute celery and onion together.
Place in layers; sprinkle top layer with stuffing mix.
Cover and bake 20 minutes at 350°, then uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: strawberry cream
directions: Freeze banana halves until firm.
Combine all ingredients and blend until smooth.
Serve in tall glasses.
Has 155 calories and 80 mg sodium.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini into thin slices.
Put squash into buttered casserole dish.
Cook remaining ingredients for 5 minutes.
Pour over squash and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: betsy's microwave sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first four ingredients and cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Toss 1 cup of crumb mixture with the yams and cranberries or crushed pineapple.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake in microwave oven at Medium-high for about 15 minutes, until hot throughout.
Top with remaining crumb mixture, sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups miniature marshmallows and broil in oven until lightly browned.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: chicken succotash stew
directions: In 8-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, cook bacon until browned.
Remove bacon to paper towels to drain.
Spoon off all but 1 tablespoon bacon drippings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Make into balls.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, turning over after 10 minutes.
Freezes well, but do not bake before freezing.
Good and these are not dry!

title: pink shrimp dip
directions: Blend cheese with seasonings; mix in shrimp.
Serve as a dip for crackers, potato chips, celery or carrot sticks.
Good for stuffing celery.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and creamed margarine together.
Add one egg at a time to the mixture, beating after each addition.
Mix in sugar, flour and extracts.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on a rack.
This makes a large cake.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in warm water. Add remaining ingredients. Freeze. (Keeps up to 1 month.) Just before serving, thaw to slush. Add 3 bottles ginger ale to
2 quarts of the mixture. Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: polish enchiladas(servings:  12 enchiladas)
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream, cumin, salt and pepper and chilies together.
Warm tortillas until flexible.
Fill each tortilla with a little chicken mixture and a little cheese.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour gravy mixture over enchiladas and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: helen robert heath cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and oleo thoroughly; set aside 1/2 cup of mix for top.
Now in batter add well-beaten egg, milk, soda, salt and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan, then add (layered) pecans and Heath or Skor bars.
Lastly, sprinkle reserved mix over Heath bars.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: memaw's peanut butter ice cream
directions: Pour a
little milk in saucepan.
