Add peanut butter and stir until melted.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large stock pot.
Simmer slowly, while stirring, for 1 hour or more.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
May be mixed together and refrigerated until ready to cook.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
(Optional:
Add strawberries.) Let thicken, but not completely.

title: shepherd's pie with cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Mash with milk, butter, cheese, salt and pepper.
Reserve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream egg, shortening, powdered sugar, vanilla, salt, soda and cream of tartar together.
Add flour.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mom's barbecue beans
directions: Drain beans. Brown meat thoroughly and add onions (optional for flavor). Mix all ingredients in boiler and simmer over medium heat for 1 hour. Stir occasionally.

title: mother's marshmallow creme fudge candy
directions: Cook milk and sugar, stirring constantly, 15 minutes after comes to a boil.
Add butter, chocolate chips, a pinch of salt, pecans, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Spoon on waxed paper.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add Sprite.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain green beans, peas, corn and pimentos.
Dice green pepper, celery and onion.
Heat for dressing and cool: sugar, salt, pepper, salad oil, vinegar and water.
Pour dressing over combined vegetables.
Let set overnight.
Keeps several days in refrigerator and can be frozen.

title: apple crunch
directions: Peel and slice 3 large apples.
Place in well-greased pan. Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: mother's sweet potato croquettes
directions: Mash potatoes.
Form into balls around a marshmallow.
Roll in melted butter and roll in corn flakes.
Bake on broil until toasted on all sides.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries. Add sugar and chill, covered, overnight. Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in unsweetened whipped cream. Chill before serving. Will keep for several days, covered, in refrigerator.
Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: canadian shortbread
directions: Beat butter with a mixer until foamy like cream. (Do not use margarine.) Sift dry ingredients into butter a small amount at a time. Beat well after each addition. Add vanilla. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 20 minutes or until slightly golden at 300°. Do not overbake.

title: gail's special chutney
directions: Peel and coarsely chop tomatoes, apples and onions.
Combine all ingredients in stainless steel or enamel pot and slowly bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until mixture is thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Remove chutney from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Spoon into hot sterilized jars and seal immediately.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: maple syrup cookies
directions: Cream butter and syrup and beat well.
Blend in dates, nuts and coconut; add dry ingredients.
Blend in boiling water.
Chill 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets and bake about 12 minutes or until light brown. Bake at 350°.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: texas trash
directions: Simmer first five ingredients in skillet 5 minutes stirring constantly. Mix together all other ingredients, then pour first mixture over this and mix well. Bake at 250 degrees for 1-2 hours stirring every 20 minutes. Store in tightly covered containers. This recipe is easier if you split it up and make in 2 batches.

title: italian beef
directions: Roast meat (season with garlic salt) in 325° oven until medium rare.
Remove meat; cool and slice thin on electric slicer.
Add water to pan drippings, then add bouillon, seasonings and green pepper.
If desired, add 1 small clove crushed garlic.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add thinly sliced meat.
Cover and marinate 4 to 5 hours in refrigerator; freeze if desired.
Serve hot on Italian bread.
We add extra oregano to taste.

title: caramel morsel bars
directions: Melt caramels with water over low heat.
Stir until smooth. Mix cereal and peanuts in separate bowl.
Pour melted caramels over cereal mixture and stir until well coated.
Press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips over.
Melt in 200° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread melted chips evenly.

title: raspberry champagne punch
directions: In punch bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight. To serve:
Slowly pour in champagne.
Mix gently.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add cranberry sauce and whip to dissolve. Cool.
Add apples, celery and nuts.
Chill.
May be served in squares on lettuce, top with salad dressing if desired.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar, salt, pepper and yellow food coloring until well blended and add to potato mixture (potatoes, eggs, celery and onion) and stir well.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: dieter's delight
directions: Place cottage cheese in large bowl.
Pour Jell-O over and mix. Add pineapple and oranges.
Mix gently.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Keep stored in refrigerator.

title: christmas bark candy
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, heat chips and oil at 70% power for 1 minute; stir.
Microwave 10 to 20 seconds longer or until chips are melted, stirring occasionally.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Stir in baking bits or pretzels.
Spread onto a waxed paper-lined baking sheet. Chill for 10 minutes.
Remove from the refrigerator; break into pieces.
Store in an airtight container at room temperature. Yield:
about 1 pound.

title: tortilla round-ups
directions: Stir together the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon Pace picante sauce, sour cream and lemon or lime juice. Add chopped onions and green chilies. Blend.
Spread mixture on soft, flexible tortillas (at room temperature).
Firmly roll tortillas.
Put rolls in large plastic bag in refrigerator and cool overnight.
To serve, cut in 1-inch lengths.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: oriental hot and sour soup
directions: In a 3 1/2 or 4-quart crockery cooker, combine broth, bamboo shoots, water chestnuts, mushrooms, tapioca, vinegar, soy sauce, sugar and pepper. Cover; cook on low heat setting for 9 to 11 hours or on high heat setting for 3 to 4 hours. Add shrimp and tofu. Cover; cook on low or high heat setting for 50 minutes more. Pour egg slowly into cooker; stir until egg cooks and shreds. Top with parsley. Makes 8 appetizer servings.

title: graham delights
directions: Mix all ingredients together except powdered sugar.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: waldorf brown rice salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions (without butter or salt).
Cool.
Wash, core and slice apples coarsely, without peeling.
Sprinkle apples with lemon juice and toss.
Add cooked rice, celery, nuts and raisins.
Blend well.
Fold mayonnaise into yogurt.
Add to rice mixture.

title: glazed chicken drumsticks
directions: Place drumsticks in ungreased baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients; pour over drumsticks.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Line broiler pan with aluminum foil.
Place drumsticks on rack in broiler pan.
Brush drumsticks with remaining sauce.
Cook on 375° oven until done, 50 to 60 minutes, turning drumsticks once or twice.

title: pink angel cake(easter dessert)
directions: Thaw strawberries and drain off juice.
Sprinkle gelatin over juice in a small dish.
Allow to stand until gelatin is softened. Set dish in hot water until gelatin dissolves.
Combine gelatin mixture with berries.
Chill until thickened but not congealed.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and salt in saucepan. Bring to rolling boil. Boil for 5 minutes. Take off stove. Drop in oleo and vanilla. Mix well. Add oatmeal. Drop on wax paper.

title: spaghetti sauce (marinara)
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil in a saucepan. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for at least 20 minutes.
For variety, add your favorite meat, poultry or vegetables to this basic red sauce.

title: stuffed cabbage(mishee malfoof)
directions: Brown pine nuts in butter.
Put meat, rice, salt, pepper and cumin in large bowl.
Mix well.
Add pine nuts and 1/2
can tomato paste.
Mix well.
Prepare cabbage-wash and cut out the core. Place in boiling water to loosen leaves.
Do not cook.
Trim off coarse parts of leaves.
Split big leaves in half & trim thick vein.
Reserve trimming.
Place stuffing across width of a leaf and roll from bottom side up. Roll like a cigar.
Do not tuck in ends.
Squeeze closed with your hand.
Line the pot with leaf trimmings and rejected large leaves.
Arrange rolls evenly in layers in the pot.
Chop garlic and place on top of rolls.
Add remainder of tomato paste and 1/2 can of puree.
Add another tablespoon of salt.
Cover with boiling water and place a heavy dish on top of cabbage rolls.
Cook on medium heat for 25-30 mins. after it comes to a boil.

title: decorator icing
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg whites until frothy and slightly thickened.
Beat in sugar 1/2 cup at a time.
Continue to beat for about 5 minutes or until stiff.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift together cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add egg, milk and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in an 8-inch square pan at 425° for about 25 minutes.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Combine the cucumbers, onions, red peppers, green peppers and chopped celery and set overnight in 3/4 cup salt and 2 quarts water.

title: lo-cal cream cheese
directions: Rinse cottage cheese with cold water and drain well, pressing with a fork to squeeze.
Mix and blend well.
Refrigerate in covered container.

title: crazy crust cherry pie
directions: In a small mixer bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, water, shortening and egg.
Blend well at lowest speed. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.

title: "light" pound cake
directions: Coat bottom and sides of an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan with cooking spray; dust with flour.
Set aside.

title: best ever macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into greased (with margarine) crock-pot and top with remaining cheese. Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.
As good as oven baked.

title: carolyn stanley's mama's pull-apart bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/3
cup warm water and sugar.
Put 4 cups warm water in
large mixing bowl (size of small dishpan). Add salt, sugar and
oil.
Add	enough	flour to make a batter (like cake batter).
Add	yeast
mixture.
Add enough flour to handle (I never measure
it).
Put
in a large container, well oiled.
Let rise
until double in size.
Work down.
Let rise again
until double
in	size.

title: marshmallow bananas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine bananas, marshmallows, and orange juice.
Divide mixture into 4 individual oven proof serving dishes.
Bake 15 minutes, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is heated through.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from broth and debone. Return to broth and bring to a boil.
Mix Bisquick and milk until soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto boiling stew.
Add bouillon.
Cook uncovered over low heat for 10 minutes; cover and cook 10 minutes.

title: chicken breasts veronique (for two people)
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with salt.
Melt 1 tablespoon of the butter in wide frying pan over medium heat.
Add chicken breasts and cook until golden on each side.
Stir in marmalade, tarragon and wine.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes or until meat is no longer pink when slashed in thickest part.
Transfer to warm serving dish.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Mix all together. Then add it to shells. Bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pumpkin ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt cake pan or angel food pan, 10 x 4-inch.
Beat ingredients, except glaze, on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat again on medium speed for three minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Spread in pan.

title: holiday cranberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Strain through a cheesecloth if desired.
Chill. Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.
Makes about 5 quarts or 42 (4-ounce) servings.

title: spam casserole
directions: Dice Spam.
Saute in oil.
Add onion.
Saute until tender. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly in pan or place in a 350° oven until hot.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese until creamy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with strawberries and glaze.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spray muffin tins lightly with Pam. Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg whites, honey and applesauce.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin tins.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix.
Pour into 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle on top with nutmeg.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop dates, cherries and nuts in large bowl. Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt over dates, cherries and nuts. Mix by hand until fruit and nuts are covered. Beat eggs until foamy. Stir in mixture and mix well. Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. I put wax paper in bottom of pan before baking.

title: orange snack cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 55 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: barbecue cups
directions: You will need a muffin pan.

title: seafood lasagna(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Cook noodles; place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook onion in butter; add cream cheese and cottage cheese, egg, basil, salt and pepper.
Spread half of mixture over noodles.
Combine soup, milk and wine.
Stir in crab meat and shrimp.
Spoon half of this mixture over cheese layer.
Repeat all layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake, uncovered.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with sharp cheese.
Brown under broiler.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: one crust apple pie
directions: Mix in a bowl.
Slice apples, flour and sugar.
Put in uncooked pie crust.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: marie's shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cherry strawberry salad
directions: Cook strawberries in the water until soft.
Add 1 cup sugar and cook about 5 minutes.
Pour over cherry jello.
Cook until it sets, then add the celery, apple and nuts.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until golden brown and firm. Serve with raw vegetables or bread chunks.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: hamburger spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook meat, onions and garlic salt together, then drain.
Cook spinach until tender, drain. Combine meat, spinach, soup, mushrooms and sour cream in a 2 qt. casserole dish.
Top with cheese.

title: dog bones
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick and cut out shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Yields approximately 4 dozen.
Really are for doggies, and don't taste too bad, just not sweet.

title: best brownies
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Add eggs using a wooden spoon; beat well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually blend in egg mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yields 16 squares.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onions, celery and green pepper in oil.
Brown turkey or beef until done.
Mix all together and bake in oven at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
For last 10 minutes, add cheese and Parmesan on top and complete baking.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Do not beat.
Frost with Cool Whip when cool.

title: four egg sponge cake
directions: Separate egg yolks from whites.
Beat whites until they are stiff.

Gradually add sugar, beating well until sugar is dissolved. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Fold in sifted dry ingredients, then butter which has been melted in the water or milk.
Note dry ingredients should be sifted 3 times to properly blend them together.
Pour mixture into a 2 x 8-inch cake pan, nonstick or lined with baking paper.
Bake in moderate oven for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Turn onto cake cooler and when cold, fill the center with stiffly beaten cream.
Decorate top either with icing or beaten cream and strawberries.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding by directions on box.
Layer graham crackers and bananas (sliced).
Add pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: supreme fruit salad
directions: Drain
juice
from
fruit
cocktail.
In large bowl mix fruit cocktail, marshmallows and chopped pecans.
In separate bowl
whip cream
until stiff and then add vanilla and sugar. Mix
well. Add cream mixture to bowl with fruit and mix well. Set
in refrigerator
for 1 hour before serving.
Just before serving, add
sliced
bananas
and
mix well.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: swedish bean salad
directions: Mix green beans, onions, cucumber, salt, pepper and dill. Toss with dressing of mayonnaise and sour cream. Cover and chill several hours. May be used as salad or vegetable.

title: rainbow vegetable lasagna
directions: Saute mushrooms in cooking spray and set aside. Cook carrots in cooking spray and set aside. Cook frozen spinach and strain as much water out as possible.

title: roast beef and filling balls
directions: Brown meat in butter on top of stove.
Put in roaster with seasonings.
Dice onion and add to meat.
Add water; cover and roast 2 1/2 hours.
About 3/4 hour before meat is done, add filling balls.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Cover pork chops with sauce and bake for about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream the sugar and butter.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed sugar and butter mixture. Add sour cream and one egg at a time.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup cake mix; combine rest with butter and egg. Mix until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until light brown.

title: moon rocks
directions: Mix sugar, water, margarine, cocoa, peanut butter and salt together in a pot.
Bring this to a full rolling boil over medium heat.
Boil the mixture for one minute.
Then, take off the heat. Mix the oatmeal, dry milk and raisins together.
Add this to the hot mixture.
Stir until mixed.
Add the vanilla and mix it in well.
Drop teaspoons of cookie batter onto waxed paper or a clean tabletop.
Let the cookies cool until they are set.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pie filling mix and coffee.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer and let stand 10 minutes to soften before serving.
Top with fudge sauce.

title: creamy lemon pudding cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Mix crumbs, margarine & 1 Tbsp sugar.
Press firmly into 9 inch spring form pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and oleo.
Press into bottom and sides of pan (9-inch spring-form pan).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Add pecans on top of crumbs.
In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, melt caramels with milk over low heat.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in chocolate.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill.

title: crab treats
directions: Mix all ingredients (except the muffins!) together using a hand mixer.
Spread on separated muffins.
Cut each muffin into 6 pieces.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 72 hors d'oeuvres.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, bread, onion and green pepper. Combine with egg, tomato sauce and bread crumbs. Shape into loaf and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spicy molasses cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add molasses, spices and vanilla, then egg.
Stir soda into 3 tablespoons water and add to batter. Add flour and mix well.
Chill overnight.
Roll dough thin; cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
This dough keeps for several days in refrigerator. Yield:
4 to 5 dozen.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Cut and scrape corn from cob into a bowl. Add remaining ingredients. Place into well-greased shallow baking dish. Butter should be dotted on top. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve hot. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Shape sausage into 1-inch balls.
Cook sausage and onion in skillet until onion is tender and sausage is lightly browned; drain.
Add next 4 ingredients; heat to boiling and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. Add peas and pimento.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes longer. Taste for seasoning. Some salt and pepper may be needed, depending on seasonings in sausage.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chip crunchies
directions: In large pan, melt peanut butter and chocolate chips over low heat. Remove from heat and stir in corn flakes with wooden spoon. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet and cool.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Put hash browns, butter and clams in 6-quart kettle.
Add water to cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add milk and garlic powder. Simmer 10 more minutes, stirring often.
Add bacon, salt and pepper. Stir.
Serve with crusty bread.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut wing tips off at the joint.
Cut each wing in half at joint.
In Dutch oven, in hot oil and high heat, cook chicken wings and green onions, stirring constantly, for 7 minutes. Reduce heat to medium.
Add soy sauce and remaining ingredients. Stir well.

Cover and cook for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Uncover and cook for 10 minutes longer, stirring frequently, until almost all liquid is absorbed (18 drumettes can be substituted for chicken wings).

title: peach carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly beat together eggs in small bowl; set aside.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg into large mixing bowl.
Stir to blend. Add pureed figs, beaten eggs, carrots, peaches, raisins and nuts. Stir until blended.
Turn into an 8-inch square pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done in center.
Yields 12 squares.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Melt a little butter to grease bottom of very hot skillet. Cut chicken into squares.
Add chicken and toss with a fork. Slice and add remaining ingredients in order, tossing after each addition.
Cover skillet with lid; reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes.
Remove lid and shake on soy sauce and garlic powder to taste.
Simmer about 5 more minutes.
Serve on top of white rice.

title: whole wheat carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in whole wheat flour.
In mixer, beat sugar, oil and eggs until well blended.
Add carrots; mix well.
Add flour mixture. Batter will be thin.
Bake in a 10-inch Bundt pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: casserole, chicken
directions: Cook chicken until done.
In large bowl, mix stuffing mix, celery, salt and pepper and sage (using broth from chicken).
Mix until all is soft.
Pick chicken from bone.
Spray 9 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan with Pam.
Make layers of chicken and mushroom soup; then put dressing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° until brown (45 minutes).
Serves 6.

title: amaretto hot fruit compote
directions: Drain fruits, reserving syrup for other uses.
Combine canned fruits in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine bananas and lemon juice and toss gently.
Add to fruit mixture.

title: butter rolls
directions: Mix flour, shortening and milk well.
Get small pieces of dough.
Roll thin.
Put a teaspoon of butter on the strip and roll up.
Put a tablespoon of sugar and a few drops of vanilla on the roll.
Put in baking dish.
Cover rolls with milk.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 300° for about 35 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spray large roasting pan with Pam.
Place popcorn and nuts in pan.
Place in oven at 250° while cooking other ingredients.
Cook sugar, oleo, syrup and salt at rolling boil for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and soda; stir well and pour over warm corn and nuts. Place in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on wax paper and break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Combine oats, brown sugar, corn syrup, butter, peanut butter and vanilla, mixing well.
Press into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately place chocolate pieces on top.
Let stand 5 minutes or until chocolate is softened, then spread evenly over entire surface.
Cut into bars while still warm.
Cool.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: easy caramel pecan rolls
directions: Mix pecans, 2/3 cup brown sugar, corn syrup and melted margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread to cover bottom of pan and set aside.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, making two 8-inch layers.
When cool, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream, and coconut, blend well and chill.
Reserve one cup of sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread remainder of sour cream mixture between layers of cake.
Combine reserved sour cream mixture with Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth, spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal cake in air tight container and refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: golden lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then flour.
In skillet, melt margarine. Brown chicken on all sides over medium heat.
Stir in soup mix, blended with water, and lemon slices.
Cover chicken with sauce (sauce will thicken).
Can add onion, sliced carrots and a few garlic bulbs.
Serve over rice.

title: sugarless ice cream
directions: Taste before freezing for sweetness. Freeze in ice cream churn.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Cream sugar and butter.
Mix in egg and flavoring; measure flour.
Blend dry ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Divide dough in half and roll out on floured surface to 3/6 inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Sprinkle with sugar. Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Add butter and vanilla and blend well.
Pour into baked pie shell; top with meringue and bake at 300° until brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan or muffin pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: burgoo
directions: Combine first 12 ingredients in a stock-pot or roaster. Simmer 4 hours or until meat falls from bones.
Cool.
Strain the stock and remove chicken from bones.
Refrigerate meat and stock until next day.

title: quick pork chop dinner
directions: Spread mustard over chops; sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Melt margarine and brown chops thoroughly in skillet. Add chicken rice soup and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: 6-kid dessert
directions: Combine whipped cream, marshmallows and butter mints in large mixing bowl.
Place 1/2 of crushed cookies in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer the other ingredients on top.
Cover with the rest of the crushed cookies.
Refrigerate until ready to eat. Yield:

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all pie ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes, or until firm and brown.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Punch holes in cake with a fork.
Mix milk and cream of coconut.
Pour over cake.
Let cool. Then put Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: cole slaw
directions: Layer the ingredients until all are used.

title: meridian cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients in large punch bowl.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Chop onions, bell pepper and celery with 1/2 stick of butter, saute in frying pan.
Add juice from mushrooms and 4 teaspoons of butter.
Stir.
Add sliced mushrooms and milk.
Stir; let cook 5 to 10 minutes on medium heat.
Stir in cayenne pepper.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add beaten eggs, lemon juice and flour.
Stir in the crab meat and bread crumbs and cook 5 minutes.
Stuff crab shells or pour into casserole dish.
Brown in oven and serve.

title: olga's pound cake
directions: Sift flour 5 times before measuring.
Cream Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat for 1 minute after each egg.
Add salt and vanilla to egg mixture.
Add flour gradually.
Bake at 350° for exactly 1 hour in tube pan.
Preheat oven.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and put in buttered casserole.
May add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg.
May add orange juice.

title: olives
directions: Mix with fingers.
Roll around olives.
Bake at 400° until light brown, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Cook chicken and remove the bones. Place chicken pieces in bottom of a baking dish (a shallow dish works best). Reserve stock. In a small amount of reserved stock, cook until tender the onion and celery. Combine soups and milk and add to the mixture. Pour mixture over chicken. Cover chicken with stuffing mix. Heat 1 3/4 cups reserved stock with margarine and pour over stuffing. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375° or until hot and bubbly.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: tortilla roll-up
directions: Mix ingredients, sour cream, cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, green onions, pimentos and garlic salt.
Spread mixture on tortillas.
Roll up and chill tortillas.
Cut tortillas in 3/4-inch slices.
Serve with salsa for dipping.

title: breast of chicken magnifique
directions: Brown chicken in butter in a large skillet.
Remove from skillet and brown mushrooms.
Stir in soup, garlic and seasonings. Return chicken.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend in cream; heat slowly.
Serve with wild rice mix.
Garnish with toasted, slivered almonds.
Serves 8.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and egg.
Add flour and dry ingredients.
Add bananas and beat.
Add chocolate chips. Bake in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
When smooth, stir in vanilla.
Place cereal in large Ziploc bag.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal; seal bag and shake until all cereal is covered.
Add powdered sugar and shake again until covered. Spread on waxed paper until cool.
Store in tightly covered container.
Enjoy.

title: mom's no bake cookies
directions: Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and cool.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Break the pork sausage into small bits and fry in a heavy skillet until lightly browned.
Add the ground ham, corned beef, chopped onion and parsley and continue to cook, stirring frequently with a fork, until hot.
Sift the flour, salt and dry mustard together, then add the meat to the mixture, stirring to combine. Add the milk and continue to cook over low heat until the mixture is thickened.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in the chopped sauerkraut and mix well.
Chill the mixture thoroughly.
Shape the mixture into 4-inch balls.
Roll the balls lightly in flour. Combine the beaten eggs, water and salt to make an egg batter.
Dip the floured balls into the egg batter, then in the fresh bread crumbs.
Deep-fry in 360° oil for 1 1/2 minutes or until the balls are a golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper and serve hot.
Dill sauce makes a great sauce to serve with these balls.
To reduce fat:
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes rather than deep-frying. Extra balls may be stored in a tightly closed container and reheated in the microwave.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix well beaten eggs with sugar.
Add melted margarine, then add coconut, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for about 40 minutes.

title: lasagna swirls
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Rinse thoroughly with cold water and drain.

Mix together spinach, 3/4 cup of the Parmesan cheese, Ricotta, salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and nutmeg. Spread 1/3 cup cheese mixture along entire length of each noodle, roll noodles up and stand on end in buttered 7 to 8-inch casserole at least 2 1/2 inches deep with a small amount of sauce.
Pour sauce over noodles.
Cover and refrigerate if made ahead.
May be frozen also.
Bake, covered, in 350°
oven until rolls are heated through, about 30 minutes (50 to 60 minutes if cold).
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 round cake pans according to package instructions.
Cool and refrigerate to chill.
Cut 1 layer into small pieces and place in a punch bowl.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add condensed milk and beat.
Add lemon juice and a few drops food coloring.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Pour in crust. Beat egg whites with sugar and vanilla; put on top.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Cool before cutting.
Freezes well.

title: peach-almond fizz
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in an electric blender.
Process until smooth. Pour 1/2 cup into each of 6 glasses.
Add 1/4 cup sparkling water. Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix all ingredients in a bowl with a wooden spoon. Pour into a greased mini-muffin pan, filling each cup 2/3 full. Bake 12-15 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen. Garnish each muffin with a pecan half if desired.

title: green chili rice
directions: Do not combine this recipe until ready to bake.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Lightly spray baking dish with Pam.
Break eggs into dish. Break yolks, but do not stir.
Layer with browned and drained sausage, cheese and drained mushrooms.
Pour whipping cream evenly over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour, uncovering after approximately 45 minutes.

title: salt map
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and add liquids.
